description: Vijayaraghavan is an Indian actor who predominantly works in Malayalam cinema. He is popular for his character roles. He is the son of popular drama and cinema artist N. N. Pillai.

Name: Vikas Kalantri
description: Vikas Kalantri is a Hindi actor who has done many films such as Dil Bechara Pyaar Ka Mara, where he appeared alongside actor Mallika Kapoor and others. He has also done films such as Nayee Padosan and Jigyaasa.

Name: Vikas Sethi
description: Vikas Sethi is an Indian actor. He played the lead role in the 2003 adult drama film Oops!, he went on to play supporting roles in numerous hit TV series and Bollywood films.

Name: Vikram Gokhale
description:
Vikram Gokhale is an Indian film, television and stage actor, notable for his roles in Marathi theatre and Hindi films and television. He is the son of another well-known veteran Marathi theater and film actor, Chandrakant Gokhale.
Gokhale made his directorial debut in 2010, with the Marathi film Aaghaat.

Name: Vikram Kennedy
description: Kennedy John Victor, better known by his stage name Vikram or Chiyaan Vikram, is an Indian actor and singer who predominantly appears in Tamil language films.

Name: Vikram Prabhu
description: Vikram Prabhu is an Indian film actor working in Tamil language films who made his debut in Prabhu Solomon's Kumki. He also played the protagonist in Ivan Veramathiri and Vellaikaara Durai. He is the son of actor Prabhu Ganesan and grandson of the actor Sivaji Ganesan.

Name: Vikranth
description: Vikranth is an Indian film actor who has appeared in Tamil language films. He was first introduced in the film Karka Kasadara directed by R. V. Udayakumar and later appeared in other romantic drama films.

Name: Vimal
description: Vimal is an Indian film actor, who appears in Tamil films. Following uncredited appearances and a cameo role in the critically acclaimed movie Kanchivaram, he played the lead role in Pandiraj's critically acclaimed Pasanga. Subsequently, he played lead roles in several low-budget productions.

Name: Vinay Apte
description: Vinay Apte was an Indian film and television actor. He acted in several Marathi movies and television shows in his almost 40-year-old career. He has also acted in Hindi movies such as Chandni Bar, Ek Chalis Ki Last Local, It's Breaking News, Satyagraha and Rajneeti.

Name: Vinay Pathak
description: Vinay Pathak is an Indian actor. He has starred in many films including Khosla Ka Ghosla, Bheja Fry, Island City and Johnny Gaddaar and had a supporting role movies like Jism and Rab Ne Bana Di Jodi.

Name: Vinay Virmani
description: Vinay Virmani is a Canadian actor. Virmani was born in Brampton and raised in Toronto. After graduating in business from York University, Virmani studied filmmaking and theatre at Lee Strasberg Theatre and Film Institute in New York City.

Name: Vinayak Joshi
description: Vinayak Joshi is an Indian film, television, web-series and theatre actor, Winner of best director in Thespo8. Former Radio jockey, Former Head of Digital communication at Flipkart, host of Saregamapa season 6, lead host of IPL 2019 in Starsports kannada.

Name: Vindu Dara Singh
description: Virendra Singh Randhawa better known as Vindu Dara Singh is an Indian film and television actor. He is the winner of the third season of Bigg Boss.

Name: Vineeth
description: Vineeth Radhakrishnan is an Indian film actor, classical dancer and voice artist, known for his works predominantly in Malayalam and Tamil films. He has also starred in a few Telugu, Kannada and Bollywood films.

Name: Vineet Kumar Singh
description: Viineet Kumar is an Indian film actor and writer. After few series of performances in his early career including the 2010 film City of Gold, he got noticed for his role in films like Bombay Talkies and Gangs of Wasseypur.

Name: Vineeth Sreenivasan
description: Vineeth Sreenivasan is an Indian playback singer, actor, film director, screenwriter, producer, lyricist, creative director and dubbing artist. He works in Malayalam cinema. Vineeth is son of the actor-screenwriter Sreenivasan.

Name: Vinod Khanna
description: Vinod Khanna was an Indian actor, film producer and politician. He was the recipient of two Filmfare awards. He was also an active politician and was the MP from the Gurdaspur constituency between 1998–2009 and 2014–2017.

Name: Vinod Mehra
description: Vinod Mehra was an Indian actor in Bollywood films. He started out as a child actor in the late 1950s before starting his film career as an adult in 1971. He acted in over 100 films from the 1970s through to his death at the age of 45 in 1990.

Name: Vipin Sharma
description: Vipin Sharma is an Indian film actor known for his works predominantly in Hindi cinema. He is an alumnus of National School of Drama, New Delhi, India and the Canadian Film Centre, Toronto, Ontario, Canada.

Name: Vishal Krishna
description: Vishal Krishna Reddy is an Indian film actor and producer who works in the Tamil film industry. The younger son of film producer G. K. Reddy, Vishal studied Visual Communications at Loyola College, Chennai. Best known for his roles in action films, he produces films under his production company, Vishal Film Factory.

Name: Vishal Karwal
description: Vishal Karwal is an Indian television-film actor. He has played some of the famous serials like Bhagyavidhaata, Rishton Se Badi Pratha and Rangrasiya. He participated in MTV Roadies, MTV Splitsvilla and Bigg Boss. He has also appeared in a lead role in Vikram Bhatt's horror thriller 1920 London in 2016.

Name: Vishnu Manchu
description:
Vishnu Manchu is an Indian film actor, producer and director known for his works in Telugu cinema and television.
He had a brief stint as a child artist with the 1985 film Ragile Gundelu. Years later, he starred in the 2003 Telugu action film Vishnu, for which he won the Filmfare Best Male Debut.

Name: Vishnu Vishal
description: Vishnu Vishal is an Indian actor and producer who appears in Tamil language films. After a brief career in cricket, he started his acting career in the year 2009 playing the lead role in the sports film Vennila Kabadi Kuzhu, winning acclaim for his portrayal.

Name: Vishnuvardhan
description: Dr.Vishnuvardhan, born Sampath Kumar, was an Indian film actor predominantly in Kannada cinema. He appeared in over 220 films in Kannada, Hindi, Telugu, Tamil and Malayalam. He was called 'The Phoenix of Indian Cinema'. He made his debut in the 1972 film, Vamsha Vriksha, in a supporting role.

Name: Vivek
description: Vivekanandan, known by his stage name Vivek, is an Indian film actor, comedian, television personality, playback singer and activist working in the Tamil film industry.

Name: Vivek Oberoi
description: Vivek Oberoi is an Indian film actor. He made his film debut with Ram Gopal Varma's Company which won him two Filmfare Awards.

Name: Vivek Mushran
description: Vivek Mushran is an Indian actor. After leaving Sherwood College, Nainital, he started his career in 1991 with the blockbuster Hindi movie Saudagar and has appeared in many other movies, including Ram Jaane, the Sachin-directed Aisi bhi kya jaldi hai, First Love Letter, and Anjaane.

Name: VTV Ganesh
description: Ganesh Simbhu, also known by his stage name VTV Ganesh is an Indian actor, comedian and film producer. He is best known for his hoarse voice, and his appearances in films featuring Silambarasan. He had made his debut in Tamil movie Red directed by Singampuli.

Name: Yash Gowda
description: Naveen Kumar, known by his stage name as Yash, is an Indian film actor from Kannada cinema. He is known for his roles in the movies Rajadhani, Mr. and Mrs. Ramachari, Kirataka, K.G.F: Chapter 1. His latest film K.G.F: Chapter 2 is scheduled to be released on October 23, 2020.

Name: Yash Pandit
description: Yash Pandit is a Bollywood and television actor.

Name: Yashpal Sharma
description: Yashpal Sharma is an Indian Bollywood actor and theatre artist. He is best known for his role as Randhir Singh in Sudhir Mishra's 2003 Hindi movie Hazaaron Khwaishein Aisi, apart from Lagaan, Gangaajal, Ab Tak Chhappan, Apaharan, Singh Is Kinng, Aarakshan and Rowdy Rathore.

Name: Yash Tandon
description: Yashpal Tandon is a Ugandan policymaker, political activist, professor, author and public intellectual. He has lectured extensively in the areas of International Relations and Political economy. He was deeply involved in the struggle against the dictatorship of Idi Amin in 1970's Uganda and has spent time in exile.

Name: Yash Tonk
description: Yash Tonk is an Indian actor from Sonipat District, Haryana. He was brought up at Hisar, Haryana where his father works as Chief Security officer in Haryana Agricultural University, Hisar. He studied at Campus School in Hisar. He graduated from Sri Aurobindo College University of Delhi.

Name: Yatin Karyekar
description: Yatin Karyekar is a veteran Indian actor in the Bollywood film industry. He was also part of long running television serial Shanti. He appeared in the role of Aurangzeb in popular Marathi serial Raja Shivchhatrapati.

Name: Yogesh
description:
Yogesh, better known by his nick names Yogi or Loose Maada, is an Indian actor and singer who predominantly appears in Kannada language films.
Yogesh made his debut in the 2007 film Duniya where he portrayed the supporting character named "Loose Maada" and since then being referred with the same name.

Name: Yugendran
description: Yugendran is an Indian film actor and singer who has sung hundreds of songs in Tamil, Telugu and Malayalam. He is also an occasional music director and host.

Name: Zayed Khan
description: Zayed Abbas Khan is an Indian actor and producer who appears in Hindi films. He has received a Filmfare Award nomination and is the son of Bollywood actor Sanjay Khan.

Name: Zeishan Quadri
description: Zeishan Quadri is an Indian writer, actor, director and producer who has written the story and co-written the screenplay for the Bollywood crime genre film Gangs of Wasseypur, directed by Anurag Kashyap. Quadri has also acted in Gangs of Wasseypur - Part 2. He has directed and produced the film Meeruthiya Gangsters.

Name: Zubeen Garg
description: Zubeen Garg is an Indian playback singer, music director, composer, lyricist, music producer, film director, film producer, actor and philanthropist. His contributions are mostly attributed in Assamese, Bengali and Bollywood films and music.

Name: Zulfi Syed
description: Zulfi Syed also known as Zulfikar Syed is an Indian model and actor. Syed Zulfi is a former winner of Gladrags Manhunt Contest. He was a contestant in Bigg Boss.

Name: Aamna Sharif
description: Aamna Sharif, is an Indian actress known for portraying Kashish Sinha in Kahiin to Hoga and Komolika Basu /Sonalika in Kasautii Zindagii Kay.

Name: Aarathi
description: Aarathi is an Indian actress and director who works predominantly in Kannada language films. She is best known for roles during the 1970s and 1980s.

Name: Aarti Agarwal
description: Aarthi Agarwal was an Indian-American actress who primarily worked in Telugu cinema, also known as Tollywood. She was the older sister of Aditi Agarwal, also an actress. As per Idlebrain.com source, Aarthi Agarwal was top heroine in the year of 2002.

Name: Aarti Chhabria
description: Aarti Chabria is an Indian actress and former model who appears in Hindi, Telugu, Punjabi and Kannada films.

Name: Abhirami
description: Abhirami is an Indian actress and television host. She has acted in Malayalam, Tamil, Telugu and Kannada films. Her career, which started in 1995, was interrupted in 2004 when her family moved to the United States. She made a comeback in 2013.

Name: Adah Sharma
description: Adah Sharma is an Indian film actress who mainly appears in Hindi, Telugu and Tamil language films. Sharma, after finishing her schooling, made her acting debut with a leading role in the 2008 Hindi language horror film 1920, a box office success.

Name: Aditi Ravi
description: Aditi Ravi is an Indian model and actress, who appears in Malayalam films. She pursued a career in modelling before becoming an actress, debuting with a commercial for The Times of India during her college education. She made her acting debut with the 2014 film Angry Babies in Love, in a supporting role.

Name: Aditi Sharma
description: Aditi Sharma is an Indian television actress known for playing Meera Dhingra in Kaleerein and Roshni Ahmad in Yehh Jadu Hai Jinn Ka!.

Name: Aditi Govitrikar
description: Aditi Govitrikar is an Indian model, actress and a doctor. From 1997 until 2004, Govitrikar remains the only Indian supermodel with the both medical doctor and psychologist qualification. She has been touted by Hindustan Times as "Beauty with Brains". She is a vegetarian and ardent Vipassana practitioner.

Name: Aditi Rao Hydari
description: Aditi Rao Hydari is an Indian actress, dancer and singer who works in Bollywood, Tamil, Malayalam and Telugu films. She made her on-screen debut with Malayalam film Prajapathi in 2006.

Name: Aditi Sarangdhar
description: Aditi Sarangdhar is a Marathi actress. She worked in many Marathi movies and series. She is famous for the role of Saloni Deshmukh in TV serial Lakshya.

Name: Ahaana Krishna
description: Ahaana Krishna is an Indian film actress who appears in Malayalam films. She made her debut in Njan Steve Lopez in 2014. Her notable work include Luca, Pathinettam Padi, Njandukalude Nattil Oridavela

Name: Aindrita Ray
description: Aindrita Ray is an Indian film actress, primarily appearing in Kannada films. She made her acting debut in 2007, starring in Meravanige and went on to appear in several commercially successful films, establishing herself as a leading contemporary actress of Kannada cinema.

Name: Aishwarya
description: Aishwarya Rai Bachchan is an Indian actress and the winner of the Miss World 1994 pageant. Through her successful acting career, she has established herself as one of the most popular and influential celebrities in India.

Name: Aishwarya Arjun
description: Aishwarya Arjun is an Indian film actress. She made her film debut in the Tamil film Pattathu Yaanai in 2013.

Name: Aishwarya Devan
description: Aishwarya Devan is an Indian film actress and Beauty queen from Kerala who has acted in Malayalam, Tamil and Kannada language films. She was crowned Femina Miss India Maharashtra 2017 and represented Maharashtra state in Femina Miss India 2017.

Name: Aishwarya Rai Bachchan
description: Aishwarya Rai Bachchan is an Indian actress and the winner of the Miss World 1994 pageant. Through her successful acting career, she has established herself as one of the most popular and influential celebrities in India.

Name: Aishwarya Rajesh
description: Aishwarya Rajesh is an Indian film actress who has appeared in leading roles primarily in Tamil cinema as well as Telugu and Malayalam films with one Hindi film. She started her career as television presenter in a comedy show called Asatha Povathu Yaaru? on Sun TV.

Name: Akanksha Juneja
description: Akanksha Juneja is an Indian television actress. She has appeared in a number of television serials and also a few films often as a vamp. She has most recently replaced actress Chahat Khanna in the role of main villain Ayesha in the famous TV series Bade Acche Lagte Hain.

Name: Aksha Pardasany
description: Aksha Pardasany is an Indian actress. She has acted in Telugu films such as Yuvatha, Ride and Kandireega.

Name: Akshara Gowda
description: Akshara Gowda is an Indian film actress who has appeared in Hindi and Tamil films. Akshara made a special appearance in Thuppakki and played a role in the festival film Chitkabrey - The Shades of Grey. She made her Bollywood debut in Priyadarshan's Rangrezz in 2013.

Name: Akshara Haasan
description: Akshara Haasan is an Indian film actress who has appeared in Hindi- and Tamil-language films. The daughter of actors Kamal Haasan and Sarika Thakur, and the younger sister of Shruti Haasan, she made her film debut with the comedy drama Shamitabh, and later appeared in Kadaram Kondan.

Name: Akshara Menon
description: Iswarya Menon is an Indian film actress who acts in Tamil, Kannada and Malayalam films.

Name: Alia Bhatt
description: Alia Bhatt is an actress and singer of Indian origin and British citizenship, who works in Hindi films. The highest-paid actress in India, as of 2019, her accolades include four Filmfare Awards.

Name: Amala
description:
Amala Akkineni is an Indian film actress, Bharata Natyam dancer, and an animal welfare activist. She acted in Tamil, Telugu, Malayalam, Kannada and Bollywood films. She has won two Filmfare Awards South One for Malayalam
and One for Telugu.

Name: Amala Paul
description: Amala Paul is an Indian film actress who works in the South Indian Film Industry. After appearing in supporting roles in the Malayalam film Neelathamara. Amala became noted after playing the title role in Mynaa, receiving critical acclaim for her work.

Name: Ambika
description: Ambika is an Indian film and television actress known for her works predominantly in Tamil, Malayalam, Kannada films and serials. She also did a few Telugu and English films. She was one of the top south Indian heroines for a decade from 1978 to 1989. Her younger sister Radha was also an actress.

Name: Ameeta
description: Ameeta is an Indian actress. She appeared in Bollywood films such as Tumsa Nahin Dekha, Mere Mehboob, and Goonj Uthi Shehnai.

Name: Ameesha Patel
description:
Ameesha Patel is an Indian actress and model who predominantly appears in Bollywood films. She has also appeared in a few Telugu and Tamil films. She has won a Filmfare Award.
Patel made her acting debut in the romantic thriller blockbuster Kaho Naa... Pyaar Hai.

Name: Amoolya
description: Amulya is an Indian film actress who appears in Kannada films. She made her debut as a child artist in the early 2000s and appeared in a lead role in 2007 with Cheluvina Chittara. She is best known for her roles in the commercially successful films Chaitrada Chandrama, Naanu Nanna Kanasu and Shravani Subramanya.

Name: Amrita Arora
description: Amrita Arora is an Indian film actress, model, TV Presenter and VJ.

Name: Amrita Prakash
description: Amrita Prakash is an Indian film actress and model. She began her acting career when she was four years old, and has acted in both Bollywood and Malayalam films. She has since, been seen in a myriad of Bollywood Films, TVCs and television reality and fiction shows.

Name: Amrita Rao
description: Amrita Rao is an Indian film actress and model. She has appeared as the leading lady in several Hindi films of Bollywood and one movie in Telugu. Rao was born and raised in Mumbai; she made her screen debut in Ab Ke Baras, for which she was nominated for the Filmfare Best Female Debut Award in 2003.

Name: Amrita Singh
description: Amrita Singh is an Indian actress. Through her films like Betaab and Mard, she gained popularity and became a well known and popular actress in the 1980s. She took a break from acting in the early 1990s for a decade and returned to acting in 2002, occasionally playing supporting roles.

Name: Amruta Khanvilkar
description: Amruta Khanvilkar Malhotra is an Indian actress. She was born in Mumbai. She worked in Hindi and Marathi movies. She is popular for her dancing and participating in Fear Factor: Khatron Ke Khiladi 10.

Name: Amyra Dastur
description: Amyra Dastur is an Indian film actress who has starred in mainly Hindi films, but has also starred in some Tamil and Telugu films. She made her Bollywood debut with Issaq, opposite Prateik Babbar.

Name: Amy Jackson
description: Amy Jackson is an English actress and model best known for her work in Indian films. She began her modelling career at the age of 16, and went on to win the Miss Teen World competition in 2009. Subsequently, director A. L. Vijay cast her as the leading lady of the Tamil language period drama Madrasapattinam.

Name: Anaika Soti
description: Anaika Soti is an Indian film actress who appears in Tamil, Telugu and Hindi films. After making her debut in Ram Gopal Varma's bilingual Satya 2, she went on to feature in Vasanthabalan's period drama Kaaviya Thalaivan, for which she was nominated for the Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actress - Tamil.

Name: Ananya
description: Ananya Panday is an Indian actress who works in Hindi films. The daughter of actor Chunky Pandey, she ventured into acting in 2019 with leading roles in the teen film Student of the Year 2 and the comedy Pati Patni Aur Woh. For the former film, she won the Filmfare Award for Best Female Debut.

Name: Anaswara Kumar
description: Anaswara Kumar is an Indian film actress, who works in the Tamil film industry. She started her career with Arivazhaghan's sports thriller Vallinam, though the romantic comedy Ego released first. She made her breakthrough portraying Mohini in the black comedy film Yaamirukka Bayamey, which became a commercial success.

Name: Anaswara Rajan
description: Anaswara Rajan is an Indian actress who is known for her work in the Malayalam and Tamil film industries. Her first movie was Udaharanam Sujatha. She made her acting debut in the Malayalam short film Globe.

Name: Andrea Jeremiah
description: Andrea Jeremiah is an Indian actress, playback singer and musician. She works predominantly in the Tamil and Malayalam film industries. She also appeared in Telugu Films. She began her career as a playback singer, and has subsequently appeared in films.

Name: Andria D'Souza
description:
Andria D'Souza aka Ria D'Souza is an Indian born in Dubai. She is a TV presenter Zee Connect, TV Anchor on Zee TV, Dubai and actor based in India, mainly active in Hindi and Malayalam films Six X.
Currently an All India Professional Congress member

Name: Anita Hassanandani Reddy
description: Anita Hassanandani is an Indian actress who has acted in multilingual films and serials. She is best known for portraying Shagun Arora in Star Plus's Yeh Hai Mohabbatein and a female shape-shifting serpent named Vishakha Khanna in Colors TV's Naagin.

Name: Anita Guha
description: Anita Guha was an Indian Bengali actress who usually played mythological characters in films. She became known for playing the title role in Jai Santoshi Maa. Previously, she had played Sita in other mythological films; Sampoorna Ramayana, Shree Ram Bharat Milap and Tulsi Vivah.

Name: Anita Raj
description: Anita Raj is an Indian actress and a daughter of Jagdish Raj, whose notable roles include Prem Geet, Kusum in Zara Si Zindagi, Anita in Zameen Aasman and Shobha in Masterji.

Name: Anjala Zhaveri
description: Anjala Zaveri is an Indian British actress. She appeared in Telugu, Hindi, Tamil, Malayalam and Kannada films.

Name: Anjali
description: Anjali is an Indian film actress and model, who predominantly appears in Tamil and Telugu films. Following a stint in modelling, she was cast in starring roles in two Telugu productions; her début film ...

Name: Anjali Devi
description: Anjali Devi was an Indian actress, model and producer in Telugu and Tamil films. She was well known for her role as the Devi Sita in Lava Kusa as well as for the titular roles in movies like Suvarna Sundari and Anarkali.

Name: Anjali Sudhakar
description: Anjali is an Indian Sandalwood movie and television actress who appeared in Kannada cinema. Her original name was Shantha, before director Kashinath named her as Anjali.

Name: Anjana Bhowmick
description: Anjana Bhowmik was an actress of Bengali cinema from the 1960s until the 1980s. She was born on 30 December 1944 in Cooch Behar. Her real name is Arati Bhowmik and nickname Babli. Her father was Bibhuti Bhusan Bhowmik. She spent her school days in Cooch Behar.

Name: Anjana Sukhani
description: Anjana Sukhani is an Indian film actress and model, who predominantly appears in Bollywood films.

Name: Anju Mahendru
description: Anju Mahendru is an Indian actress. She is best known as Reeva in Kahiin To Hoga and Kamini Gupta in Kasautii Zindagii Kay.

Name: Ankita Lokhande
description: Ankita Lokhande is an Indian film and television actress known for portraying Archana in Zee TV's Pavitra Rishta as well as participating on Colors TV's reality dance series Jhalak Dikhhla Jaa 4.

Name: Ann Augustine
description: Ann Augustine is an Indian film actress who appears in Malayalam films. She is the daughter of Malayalam actor Augustine. She made her debut in Lal Jose's Elsamma Enna Aankutty.

Name: Ansiba Hassan
description: Ansiba Hassan is a Malayalam actress, television anchor and dancer. Her first role was in the 2013 Tamil film Paranjothi, directed by Gobu Balaji.

Name: Antara Mali
description: Antara Mali is an Indian actress, director, and screenwriter, who predominantly works in Bollywood films, and has also acted in a Malayalam and Telugu film.

Name: Anu Agarwal
description: Anita Aggarwal also known as Anu Aggarwal is a former Indian model and actress. She is best known for her works in Aashiqui, The Cloud Door and Thiruda Thiruda.

Name: Anu Prabhakar
description: Anu Prabhakar, also known by her married name Anu Prabhakar Mukherjee, is an Indian film actress, who predominantly appears in Kannada films and is from Mangalore.

Name: Anu Sithara
description: Anu Sithara is an Indian film actress who appears in Malayalam cinema.

Name: Anupama Parameswaran
description: Anupama Parameswaran is an Indian film actress who predominantly appears in Telugu, Malayalam, Tamil, Kannada films.She is best known for her debut role as Mary George in the Malayalam film Premam. Later she appeared in Telugu films such as Sathamanam Bhavati and Vunnadhi Okate Zindagi.

Name: Anupama Verma
description: Anupama Verma is a model, actress, and television personality from Lucknow. She was a contestant in the reality show Bigg Boss in 2006. She was the main lead in the song Biddu Boom boom, sung by late Nazia Hassan. She has also acted in many movies and TV commercials.

Name: Anuradha Mehta
description: Anuradha Mehta is an Indian actress and former model who appeared in Telugu and Kannada films She made her debut with the Telugu movie Arya, by which she gained popularity and applause by her performance. She also appeared in some Kannada films. She disappeared later from Telugu and Kannada films.

Name: Anurita Jha
description: Anurita Jha is an Indian actress and model. She hails from Madhubani Bihar and was groomed and studied at Patna and Delhi. She has taken part in fashion weeks in Delhi as well as Mumbai.

Name: Anusha Dandekar
description: Anusha Dandekar is an Indian-Australian MTV VJ, actress and singer, who is best known as a VJ and a host who has hosted several shows.

Name: Anushka Sharma
description: Anushka Sharma is an Indian actress and film producer who works in Hindi films. One of the most popular and highest-paid actresses in India, she has received several awards, including a Filmfare Award.

Name: Anushka Shetty
description: Sweety Shetty, known by her stage name Anushka Shetty, is an Indian actress and model who predominantly works in the Telugu and Tamil film industries. She has received several accolades, including three CineMAA Awards, a Nandi Award, TN State Film Awards and three Filmfare Awards from eight nominations.

Name: Anuya Bhagvath
description: Anuya Y Bhagwat is an Indian film actress and model who has appeared in Tamil films. She is best known for her performances in Rajesh's romantic comedy Siva Manasula Sakthi and Shankar's Nanban.

Name: Aparajita Mohanty
description:
Aparajita Mohanty is an Oriya movie actress based in Bhubaneswar, Odisha, India. She is the wife of Odia actor Uttam Mohanty and mother of actor Babushan.
She received the ETV Priya Odia 2009 award.

Name: Aparnaa Bajpai
description: Aparna Bajpai is an Indian film actress who has appeared in Tamil, Hindi and Malayalam language films. She is best known for her role in the 2010 film, Easan, directed by Sasikumar.

Name: Aparna Balamurali
description: Aparna Balamurali is an Indian film actress and playback singer who works in Malayalam cinema and Tamil cinema. She is best known for her role as Jimsy in Maheshinte Prathikaaram and Anu in Sunday Holiday.

Name: Aparna Sen
description: Aparna Sen is an Indian filmmaker, screenwriter and actress who is known for her work in Bengali cinema. A leading actress of the late 1960s and 1970s she has received eight BFJA Awards, five for best actress, two for best supporting actress and one for lifetime achievement.

Name: Archana
description: Archana Shastry is an Indian film actress, working in Telugu cinema, Tamil cinema and Kannada cinema. She was one of the contestants in the first season of Bigg Boss - Telugu, hosted by N. T. Rama Rao Jr.. Shastry is a trained classical dancer in Kuchipudi dance form and performs in India, USA, UK and Malayasia.

Name: Archana Jose Kavi
description: Archana Jose Kavi is an Indian film actress and YouTuber and a television host. Her acting debut was in Neelathaamara scripted by M. T. Vasudevan Nair and directed by Lal Jose.

Name: Archana Puran Singh
description: Archana Puran Singh is an Indian television presenter and film actress. She is known for comedy roles in Bollywood movies and as a judge on comedy shows like Sony TV India's The Kapil Sharma Show.

Name: Archana Gupta
description: Archana Gupta is an Indian model and film actress. She is based out of Mumbai. She has acted in Tamil, Kannada, Malayalam, Telugu and even a Russian film. She recently acted in a web series called Poison for Zee5 along with Arbaz Khan, Rimi Sen, Freddy Daruwala, Tanuj Virwani & others.

Name: Archita Sahu
description: Archita Sahu is an Indian actress and model who works in Odia language films[Ollywood Movie]. She played the leading female role in several hit Odia films like Babu I Love You, Mu Eka Tumara, Chocolate and Akashe Ki Ranga Lagila. Besides films, she has achieved success as a model.

Name: Aruna Irani
description: Aruna Irani is an Indian actress, who has acted in over 500 films throughout Hindi, Kannada, Marathi and Gujarati cinema, playing mostly supporting and character roles.

Name: Aruna Shields
description: Aruna Shields is a British actress, filmmaker and therapist. She debuted in Bollywood with the film Prince. She is 5.6' feet tall in height.

Name: Arundathi Nag
description: Arundhati Nag is an Indian film and theatre actress. She has been involved with multilingual Theatre in India, for over 25 years, first in Mumbai where she got involved with Indian People's Theatre ...

Name: Asawari Joshi
description: Asawari Joshi is an Indian actress. She has acted in many Marathi language films and serials. She is known for her role in the Hindi TV series, Office Office. She has acted as Lovely Kapoor in Om Shanti Om, a movie which starred Shahrukh Khan.

Name: Asha Negi
description: Asha Negi is an Indian television actress. She is recognised for her roles in the shows Pavitra Rishta as Poorvi, Ek Mutthi Aasmaan as Kalpana, Kuch Toh Hai Tere Mere Darmiyaan as Koyal. She won the Indian dance reality show Nach Baliye 6 along with her partner Rithvik Dhanjani in 2014.

Name: Asha Parekh
description: Asha Parekh is an Indian film actress, director, and producer who appeared in many commercially successful films throughout her career. She was the highest paid actress of her time and was one of the most successful actresses of the 1960s and 1970s.

Name: Asha Saini
description: Flora Saini, also known by her screen name Asha Saini, is an Indian film actress and model.She predominantly works in Tollywood, and also appeared in a number of Kannada, Tamil and Hindi films as well.

Name: Ashima Bhalla
description: Ashima Bhalla is an Indian actress who has appeared in Hindi, Kannada, Tamil, Telugu and Assamese language films. Bhalla made her debut with Pyaar Zindagi Hai starring Mohnish Bahl and Rajesh Khanna.

Name: Ashwini Bhave
description: Ashwini Bhave is an Indian model and actress known for her work in both Hindi and Marathi films and television serials. Born and raised in India, she now lives in the San Francisco Bay Area.

Name: Ashwini Kalsekar
description: Ashwini Kalsekar is an Indian actress works mostly in Marathi television and film industry, later Hindi daily soaps and Known mostly for her collaboration with famous directors like Sriram Raghavan, Rohit Shetty and Ram Gopal Varma. Best role in TV serial jodha akbar.

Name: Asin Thottumkal
description: Asin Thottumkal, known mononymously as Asin, is a former Indian actress who mostly appeared in Tamil films. She also appeared in lead roles in Hindi, Telugu and Malayalam films. She is a trained Bharathanatyam dancer. She has received three Filmfare Awards.

Name: Athiya Shetty
description: Athiya Shetty is an Indian actress who appears in Bollywood films. She is the daughter of actor Suniel Shetty. She debuted in the romantic action film Hero for which she received a Filmfare award nomination for the Best Female Debut.

Name: Ayesha Jhulka
description: Ayesha Jhulka is an Indian film actress who predominantly appears in Hindi films. She has also worked in Odia, Kannada and Telugu languages films.

Name: Ayesha Takia
description: Ayesha Takia is an Indian film actress who appeared in Bollywood films. She made her film debut in Taarzan: The Wonder Car for which she won the Filmfare Best Debut Award in 2004. Her notable films also include Socha Na Tha, Dor, for which she won the Screen Award for Best Actress, and Wanted.

Name: Akanksha Puri
description: Akanksha Puri is Indian model, and film actress, known for her work in Malayalam, Tamil, and Bollywood. She made her bollywood debut with Madhur Bhandarkar's 2015 drama film Calendar Girls and is currently playing lead role of Mata AdiParashakti and her avatars in the show Vighnaharta Ganesha from 22 August 2017.

Name: Avantika Mishra
description: Avantika Mishra is an Indian actress, former model. In 2014, she signed onto 3 Telugu film projects, followed by the film Maaya. She played the lead in Meeku Meere Maaku Meme alongside Tarun Shetty; the film was released on 17 June 2016. In 2017 she appeared in Nenjamellam Kadhal.

Name: Babita
description: Babita, also known by her married name Babita Kapoor, is a former Indian actress of Sindhi and British descent, who appeared in Hindi-language films. The daughter of actor Hari Shivdasani, she is the first cousin of her contemporary actress Sadhana Shivdasani.

Name: Barkha Bisht
description: Barkha Bisht Sengupta commonly known by as Barkha Bisht is an Indian Television and Film Actress. She works in Hindi TV serials and Bengali, Hindi Movies. Barkha Bisht made her first TV appearance in Kitni Mast Hai Zindagi as Udita.

Name: Bala Hijam
description: Bala Hijam is an Indian film actress, who predominantly appears in Manipur films. Besides this, she has also acted in one Malayalam thriller road film, titled Neelakasham Pachakadal Chuvanna Bhoomi. She is recognized as one of the most successful actresses of Manipur.

Name: Barsha Priyadarshini
description: Varsha Priyadarshini is an Indian film actress, predominantly featured in Odia and Bengali movies and a former fashion model. Both Anubhav and Barsha met controversies because they had acted in some films those made in chit fund money, both of them later claimed that they were unaware about these in front of press.

Name: Barsha Rani Bishaya
description:
Barsha Rani Bishaya is an Indian actress who works in Assamese cinema. She also acted in many Mobile theatre groups of Assam. Apart from acting, she is also a Bihu dancer in Assam.
.

Name: Beena Banerjee
description: Beena Banerjee, also known as Beena or Bina, is an Indian actress in Bengali and Hindi films and television.

Name: Bhagyashree Patwardhan
description: Bhagyashree Patwardhan is an Indian actress, who appears in Hindi, Kannada, Marathi, Telugu and Bhojpuri films. She made her acting debut with the film Maine Pyar Kiya, for which she won the Filmfare Award for Best Female Debut.

Name: Bhairavi Goswami
description: Bhairavi Goswami, is an Indian actress, television host. She is passionate about animals and is an animal rights activist. Horse riding is her passion and she has seventeen horses.

Name: Bhama
description: Rekhitha R. Kurup, better known by her stage name Bhamaa, is an Indian film actress who has mainly appeared in Malayalam and Kannada language films. She made her debut in 2007 with the film Nivedyam directed by A. K. Lohithadas. In a career spanning over a decade, she has starred in over 40 films.

Name: Bhanumathi
description: P. Bhanumathi Ramakrishna was a multilingual Indian film actress, director, music director, singer, producer, book writer and songwriter. Widely known as the first female super star of Telugu cinema and South Indian film Industry, she is also known for her works in Tamil cinema.

Name: Bhanupriya
description: Bhanupriya is an Indian film actress, Kuchipudi dancer, and voice artist known for her works predominantly in Telugu cinema and Tamil cinema. She is also known for her works in a few Malayalam and Kannada films, Bollywood and television. Her acting debut was with the Tamil film Mella Pesungal.

Name: Bharathi Vishnuvardhan
description: Bharathi Vishnuvardhan, also known mononymously as Bharathi, is an Indian film actress known primarily for her work in Kannada cinema and television serials. She began her career in 1966, as a lead actress, with the Kannada movie Love in Bangalore.

Name: Bhargavi Narayan
description: Bhargavi Narayan is an Indian film actress in the Kannada film industry, and a theatre artist in Karnataka, India. Some of the notable films of Bhargavi Narayan as an actress include Eradu Kanasu, Pallavi Anupallavi, and Baa Nalle Madhuchandrake.

Name: Bhavana
description: Karthika Menon, better known by her stage name Bhavana, is an Indian film actress, who works in South Indian film industry. She has acted in Malayalam, Tamil, Kannada, and Telugu language films, and has established herself as a bankable lead actress.

Name: Bhavana (actress)
description: Karthika Menon, better known by her stage name Bhavana, is an Indian film actress, who works in South Indian film industry. She has acted in Malayalam, Tamil, Kannada, and Telugu language films, and has established herself as a bankable lead actress.

Name: Bhavana Rao
description: Bhavana Rao an Indian film actress who has appeared in Kannada and Tamil language films. She made her debut in the Kannada multistarrer Gaalipata winning critical acclaim for her performance, before playing leading roles in Kola Kolaya Mundhirika and Vinmeengal.

Name: Bhavya
description:
Bhavya, born as Bharathi, is a South Indian actress. She has acted in several Kannada and a few Tamil and Telugu movies. She was a top heroine of Kannada cinema during 1985-1992. She switched over to key supporting roles post 2000.
She is settled in Mumbai, India and travels frequently to Bangalore for her shoots

Name: Bhoomika Chawla
description: Bhumika Chawla is an Indian actress and a former model. She made her film debut in the Telugu film Yuvakudu and has since then worked in various Indian film industries and appeared in over thirty films in Telugu, Tamil, Hindi, Malayalam, Kannada, Bhojpuri, and Punjabi.

Name: Bhumi Pednekar
description: Bhumi Pednekar is an Indian actress who appears in Hindi films. After working as an assistant casting director at Yash Raj Films for six years, Pednekar made her film debut as an overweight bride in the company's romantic comedy Dum Laga Ke Haisha, which earned her the Filmfare Award for Best Female Debut.

Name: Bijoya Ray
description: Bijoya Ray was the wife of the Indian filmmaker Satyajit Ray. Their son Sandip Ray is also a film director. Bijoya and Satyajit were first cousins. After a long courtship, they were married in 1949.

Name: Bidita Bag
description: Bidita Bag is an Indian actress and a professional model. She has a varied portfolio when it comes to print advertisements, TV commercials and films. She is mostly known for her inclination towards socio-political films.

Name: Bindu Madhavi
description: Bindu Madhavi is an Indian model and film actress, working in Tamil and Telugu cinema. After starting her acting career in Telugu, she shifted to Tamil cinema where she was part of several successful films including Veppam, Kazhugu, Kedi Billa Killadi Ranga and Pasanga 2.

Name: Bipasha Basu
description: Bipasha Basu, also known by her married name Bipasha Basu Singh Grover, is an Indian film actress and model. Primarily known for her work in Hindi films, she has also appeared in Tamil, Telugu, Bengali and English films. Basu is the recipient of numerous accolades, including one Filmfare Award.

Name: Bina Rai
description: Bina Rai, aka "Beena Roy", was an Indian actress, primarily of the black and white era of Hindi cinema. She was known for her smile. She is most known for her roles in classics such as Anarkali and Taj Mahal, and won the Filmfare Award for Best Actress for her performance in the film Ghunghat.

Name: Bruna Abdullah
description: Bruna Abdullah is a Brazilian film actress, working in Bollywood. She played the role of "Mary" in the adult comedy film Grand Masti and Giselle in Punit Malhotra's I Hate Luv Storys. She has also starred in the 2012 Tamil movie Billa II.

Name: B. V. Radha
description:
Bengaluru Vijaya Radha was an Indian actress and a film producer. She began her career in the 1964 Kannada film Navakoti Narayana. She went on to play mostly supporting roles in over 300 films, 250 of which were in Kannada, and the rest in Tamil, Telugu, Malayalam, Tulu and Hindi.
She married to film director K. S. L.

Name: Carol Gracias
description: Carol Gracias is an Indian super model. She is a past winner of the coveted India's L'Oréal/Elite Look of the Year title. She participated and became the runner up in the reality show Bigg Boss in 2006.

Name: Celina Jaitley
description: Celina Jaitly is an Indian film actress who mainly appears in Bollywood films. A former beauty queen and model, she won the Miss India in 2001 and was the 4th runner-up at Miss Universe 2001. She made her acting debut with the 2003 thriller Janasheen.

Name: Charmila
description: Charmila is a popular film actress in Malayalam cinema. Apart from movies in Malayalam, she acted in Tamil, Telugu and Kannada movies. She completed almost 38 films in the Malayalam film industry, which is often referred to as Mollywood.

Name: Charmy Kaur
description: Charmy Kaur, also spelt as Charmme or Charmi, is an Indian film producer and former actress. She is well known for her works predominantly in Telugu cinema, as well as few Tamil, Malayalam, Kannada, and Bollywood films. She has appeared in more than forty films.

Name: Chaya Singh
description: Chaya Singh is an Indian film and television actress. She started her acting career in Kannada films and has worked in Tamil, Kannada, Malayalam, Telugu, Bengali and Bhojpuri films. She has a reputation of being very selective in her roles.

Name: Chetana Das
description: Chetana Das is an Indian actress from Assam. She is popular face in Assamese cinema for comic roles.

Name: Chippy
description: Chippy is an Indian actress who works in the South Indian film industry and works primarily in Malayalam and Kannada films. She won the Filmfare Award for Best Actress – Kannada & Karnataka State Film Award for Best Actress for her performance in Janumada Jodi.

Name: Chithra
description: Krishnan Nair Shantakumari Chithra, often credited as K. S. Chithra or simply Chithra, is an Indian playback singer and carnatic musician from Kerala. Chithra also sings Indian classical, devotional, and popular music.

Name: Chitrangada Singh
description: Chitrangada Singh is an Indian film actress who works primarily in Hindi cinema. She has starred in films like Yeh Saali Zindagi, Hazaaron Khwaishein Aisi, Desi Boyz, Inkaar, I, Me Aur Main and Baazaar.

Name: Chitrashi Rawat
description: Chitrashi Rawat is a former Indian hockey player, film actress and television presenter. Her film career began in 2007, when she starred as Komal Chautala, a member of the Indian women's national hockey team, in the movie Chak De India.

Name: Catherine Tresa
description: Catherine Tresa Alexander is an Indian film actress who primarily appears in Tamil, Telugu, Malayalam and Kannada films.

Name: Claudia Ciesla
description: Claudia Ciesla is a Polish-German-Indian film actress and model. best known for her work in Bollywood. She was a contestant on the Indian reality television series Bigg Boss.

Name: Deepti Sati
description: Deepti Sati is an Indian film actress who predominantly appears in Malayalam films. She has also appeared in Kannada, Marathi and Telugu films.

Name: Daisy Bopanna
description: Daisy Bopanna is an Indian actress who appears in Kannada, Hindi, Telugu and Tamil language films.

Name: Daisy Shah
description: Daisy Shah is an Indian film actress, model and dancer She has worked as an assistant to choreographer Ganesh Acharya.

Name: Daisy Irani
description: Daisy Irani is an Indian actress in Hindi and Telugu language films. She was a popular child actor in the 1950s and 1960s. She is most known for films such as Bandish, Ek Hi Raasta, Naya Daur, Hum Panchhi Ek Daal Ke, Jailor, Qaidi No 911 and Do Ustad. As a supporting actress, she acted in Kati Patang in 1971.

Name: Debashree Roy
description: Debashree Roy is an Indian actress, dancer, choreographer, politician and animal rights activist. As an actress, she is known for her work in Hindi and Bengali cinema. She has been cited as the reigning queen of Bengali commercial cinema.

Name: Deeksha Seth
description: Deeksha Seth is an Indian film actress and model. A finalist in Femina Miss India in 2009, she made her acting debut in the Telugu film Vedam.

Name: Deepa Sahi
description: Deepa Sahi is an Indian actress and producer from an Army background, who is best known for her role as Maya in the 1993 movie Maya Memsaab, opposite actor Shah Rukh Khan. She made her directorial debut with the movie Tere Mere Phere in 2011.

Name: Deepa Sannidhi
description: Deepa Sannidhi born Rahasya is an Indian actress who mainly appears in Kannada films. She made her acting debut in the 2011 film Saarathi.

Name: Deepal Shaw
description: Deepal Shaw is an Indian actress, singer and model who has worked in Bollywood movies.

Name: Deepika Chikhalia
description: Dipika Chikhlia Topiwala is an Indian actress who rose to fame playing Devi Sita in Ramanand Sagar's hit television serial Ramayan and was known for acting in other Indian historical TV serials.

Name: Deepika Padukone
description: Deepika Padukone is an Indian film actress and producer. One of the highest-paid actresses in India, her accolades include three Filmfare Awards. She features in listings of the nation's most popular personalities, and Time named her one of the 100 most influential people in the world in 2018.

Name: Deepti Naval
description:
Deepti Naval is an Indian-born American actress, director, and writer of Indian origin mostly active in Hindi cinema.
Her major contribution has been in the area of art cinema, winning critical acclaim for her sensitive and ‘close to life’ characters that emphasized the changing roles of women in India.

Name: Deepti Bhatnagar
description: Deepti Bhatnagar is an Indian former film actress and model. Her first film role came in Sanjay Gupta's Ram Shastra, also starring Jackie Shroff and Manisha Koirala. Some of her better known works include the Telugu film, Pelli Sandadi, the American film, Inferno and the Bollywood film, Mann.

Name: Delnaaz Paul
description: Delnaaz Irani is an Indian actress. Her brother is Bhakhtiyaar Irani and her sister-in-law is Tanaaz Irani.

Name: Devayani
description: Sushma Jayadev, known professionally as Devayani, is an Indian actress who predominantly acts in Tamil, Malayalam, Telugu along with a few Kannada, Hindi and Bengali films.

Name: Devika
description:
Devika or Prameela Devi was a Tamil and Telugu actress.
Devika is the granddaughter of Telugu cinema doyen and pioneer Raghupathi Venkaiah Naidu. One of her uncles was a Mayor of Chennai. Actress Kanaka is her daughter.

Name: Devika Rani Roerich
description: Devika Rani Chaudhuri, usually known as Devika Rani, was an actress in Indian films who was active during the 1930s and 1940s. Widely acknowledged as the first lady of Indian cinema, Devika Rani had a successful film career that spanned 10 years.

Name: Dharti Bhatt
description: Dharti Bhatt is an Indian TV actress. She is known for her role as Mahi in Mahisagar, as Pratibha in Kya Haal, Mr. Paanchal? and as Sewa in Roop - Mard Ka Naya Swaroop.

Name: Dia Mirza
description:
Dia Mirza is an Indian model, actress, producer, social worker and beauty queen who won the Miss Asia Pacific 2000 title. She made her acting debut with Rehnaa Hai Terre Dil Mein.
She subsequently featured in films including Dus, Lage Raho Munnabhai and Sanju.

Name: Diana Hayden
description: Diana Hayden is an Indian actress, model, and the winner of Miss World 1997 pageant. She is the third Indian woman to win the title of Miss World. She also won three subtitles during the pageant and is the only Miss World titleholder to do so. In 2008, she was a celebrity contestant in the reality show Bigg Boss.

Name: Diana Penty
description: Diana Penty is an Indian model and actress who appears in Hindi films. She began her modelling career in 2005 when she was signed up by Elite Models India. Penty made her acting debut in 2012 with the romantic comedy film Cocktail.

Name: Dimple Jhangiani
description: Dimple Jhangiani is an Indian television actress. Her first appearance in Tellywood began with her playing the role of Kanya in the serial Kuchh Is Tara on Sony Entertainment Television. Dimple Jhangiani had joined Kis Desh Mein Hai Mera Dil and played the role of Sanjana as Harshad Chopra's close friend.

Name: Dimple Kapadia
description: Dimple Kapadia is an Indian actress who predominantly appears in Hindi films. She was launched by Raj Kapoor at age 16, playing the title role in his teen romance Bobby. In that same year she married Indian actor Rajesh Khanna and retired from acting.

Name: Dipannita Sharma
description: Dipannita Sharma is an Indian actress and model.

Name: Disha Patani
description: Disha Patani is an Indian actress who works primarily in Hindi films. She began her acting career with the Telugu film Loafer, opposite Varun Tej. After making her Bollywood debut in the sports biopic M.S.

Name: Disha Vakani
description: Disha Vakani is an Indian film and television actress. She is well known for playing the role of Daya Jethalal Gada in popular daily sitcom Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah opposite Dilip Joshi.

Name: Divya Bharati
description: Divya Bharti was an Indian film actress, who starred in Hindi and Telugu motion pictures in the early 1990s. Known for her acting versatility, vivacity and beauty, she is regarded as one of the most popular and highest paid actresses of her time.

Name: Divya Dutta
description: Divya Dutta is an Indian film actress and model. She has appeared in Bollywood and Punjabi cinema, but has also appeared in Malayalam and English films.

Name: Divya Spandana
description: Divya Spandana, who was known professionally as Ramya, is an Indian film actress and politician who was the Member of Parliament in the Lok Sabha from Mandya, Karnataka. She primarily works in Kannada film industry, but also appears in Tamil and Telugu language films.

Name: Divyanka Tripathi
description: Divyanka Tripathi Dahiya, is an Indian actress who works in the Hindi television industry. She is known for playing the dual roles in Zee TV's Banoo Main Teri Dulhann and the character of Dr. Ishita Bhalla in Star Plus's Ye Hai Mohabbatein. In 2017, she won the dance reality show Nach Baliye.

Name: Elli Avram
description: Elisabet Avramidou Granlund, known professionally as Elli AvrRam, is a Swedish Greek actress and is now based in Mumbai, India. She is known for her Bollywood movie Kis Kisko Pyaar Karoon. AvrRam came to prominence after participating in the Indian reality TV show Bigg Boss.

Name: Esha Deol
description: Esha Deol is an Indian film actress and model who predominantly appears in Hindi films. The daughter of actor-politicians Dharmendra and Hema Malini, Deol made her debut in Koi Mere Dil Se Poochhe, which earned her awards and nominations including the Filmfare Award for Best Female Debut.

Name: Esha Gupta
description: Esha Gupta is an Indian film actress, Model and the winner of the Miss India International title of 2007. She has established a career in Bollywood films.

Name: Ena Saha
description: Ena Jennifer Saha, is an Indian film and television actress who predominantly appears in Bengali films and television shows.

Name: Eesha Rebba
description: Eesha Rebba is a Telugu cinema actress, known for films such as Anthaka Mundu Aa Tarvatha, Bandipotu, Oyee, Ami Thumi, Darsakudu, and Awe.

Name: Evelyn Sharma
description: Evelyn Sharma is a model and actress of Indian-German origin. She marked her film debut with the 2006, American film Turn left.

Name: Elina Samantray
description: Elina Samantray, also known as Elina, is an Indian actress. She started her career with the film Ishq Tu Hi Tu. She was the winner of the first season of the reality television show Kie Heba Mo Heroine, which was broadcast on Tarang TV.

Name: Erica Fernandes
description: Erica Fernandes is an Indian actress and model known for her portrayal of Dr. Sonakshi Bose in Kuch Rang Pyar Ke Aise Bhi and Prerna Sharma in Kasautii Zindagii Kay.

Name: Farah Naaz
description:
Farah Naaz Hashmi commonly credited as Farah is a leading Bollywood actress of the mid 1980s and early 1990s. She is the elder sister of Tabu.
Farha made her debut in "Faasle" in 1985 under the Yash Chopra films banner. She was one of the prominent actresses in Bollywood in the late eighties and early nineties.

Name: Farida Jalal
description: Farida Jalal is an Indian actress. In a film career spanning almost fifty years, Jalal acted in over 200 films in the Hindi, the Telugu, and the Tamil film industries.

Name: Fatima Sana Shaikh
description: Fatima Sana Shaikh is an Indian film actress known for her works in Hindi-language cinema, and television. Fatima appeared as a child artist in films such as Chachi 420 and One 2 Ka 4.

Name: Fatma Begum
description: Fatma Begum was an Indian actress, director, and screenwriter. She is often considered the first female film director of Indian cinema. Within four years, she went on to write, produce and direct many films.

Name: Freida Pinto
description:
Freida Selena Pinto is an Indian actress who has appeared mainly in American and British films.
Pinto rose to prominence with her film debut in the British drama Slumdog Millionaire, which is a loose adaptation of the novel Q & A by Indian author Vikas Swarup.

Name: Feryna Wazheir
description: Feryna Wazheir is a British Asian actress. She began her acting career in amateur theatre and made her break in the industry after she was discovered by Indian photographer Farrokh Chothia.

Name: Gabriela Bertante
description: Gabriela Bertante is a Brazilian model who appears in Indian films.

Name: Gajala
description: Gajala is an Indian film actress, who has appeared in Telugu, Malayalam and Tamil films. She made her debut in the Telugu film Nalo Vunna Prema in 2001.

Name: Gauhar Khan
description: Gauhar Khan is an Indian model and actress. After pursuing modeling, she made her acting debut with Yash Raj Films' Rocket Singh: Salesman of the Year.

Name: Gauri Karnik
description: Gauri Karnik is a Hindi and Marathi film actress. She is best known for her acting in Sur in 2002.

Name: Gautami
description: Gautami Tadimalla is an Indian film actress who has worked mainly in Tamil films, although she also appeared in successful Telugu, Malayalam, Hindi and Kannada films. She is also a television actress, television host, the founder of Life Again Foundation, and a costume designer.

Name: Gayathri Raguram
description: Gayathri Raguuram is an Indian choreographer and actress who has worked in the South Indian film industry. She was born to a brahmin Iyer family to choreographer Raghuram.

Name: Gayathrie
description: Gayathrie Shankar is a Tamil film actress, who appears in leading roles. She debuted in 2012 with 18 Vayasu, and is best known for her role in Naduvula Konjam Pakkatha Kaanom. She has since featured in various movies like Ponmaalai Pozhudhu, Rummy, Oru Nalla Naal Paathu Solren, Puriyatha Puthir, etc.

Name: Gayatri
description: Gayathri is an Indian actress from Punjab who is known for heroine roles in Kannada movies like Auto Raja, Vasantha Geetha, Sukha Samsarakke Hanneradu Sutragalu, Ade Kannu and Jwaalamukhi. She is the wife of actor Anant Nag.

Name: Gayatri Jayaraman
description: Gayatri Jayaraman is an Indian actress, who has appeared in predominantly Tamil, Kannada, Telugu and Malayalam language films. She began her career playing both lead and supporting roles in Tamil television series.

Name: Gayatri Joshi
description: Gayatri Joshi is a model turned former Bollywood actress. Her first and only film was Swades.

Name: Gayatri Patel
description: Gayatri Patel Bahl is an American born Indian actress, filmmaker, and Indian classical dancer, who appears in Hindi and English language films.

Name: Geeta Bali
description: Geeta Bali was an Indian film actress who appeared in Hindi language films. She was considered one of the most spontaneous and expressive stars of Bollywood for her acting.

Name: Geeta Basra
description: Geeta Basra is a British actress who has appeared in Bollywood films. She is married to Indian cricketer Harbhajan Singh.

Name: Geeta Dutt
description: Geeta Dutt was a prominent Indian playback singer and a famous Hindi and Bengali classical artist, born in Faridpur before the Partition of India. She found particular prominence as a playback singer in Hindi cinema. She also sang many modern Bengali songs, both in the film and non-film genre.

Name: Geetha
description: Geetha Kadambee is an Indian actress who appears in Malayalam, Tamil, Kannada, Telugu and Hindi films. She debuted in the Tamil film Bairavi. Since then she has acted in over 200 films in all major South Indian languages, and in a few Hindi films. She also appears in South Indian television serials.

Name: Geetu Mohandas
description: Gayathri Mohandas known professionally as Geetu Mohandas is an Indian film actress and director known for her works in Malayalam cinema and Bollywood.

Name: Genelia D'Souza
description: Genelia Deshmukh is an Indian film actress and model. She has appeared in Telugu, Hindi, Tamil, Kannada and Malayalam films. After gaining wide attention in a Parker Pen commercial with Amitabh Bachchan, Genelia began her acting career with the box-office hit Tujhe Meri Kasam in 2003.

Name: Girija
description: Girija is a Telugu film actress and comedian of 1950 and 1960s. She was born on 3 March 1938, in Kankipadu, Andhra Pradesh. Her first movie was Kasturi Sivarao's Paramanandayya Shishyula Katha. She acted in many films with Relangi Venkataramaiah and became famous hit comedian pair.

Name: Girija Shettar
description: Girija Shettar is a former Indian film actress of mixed origin, known for her works in South Indian films. In 1989, Shettar starred in Maniratnam's film Geethanjali. She then did the Malayalam film Vandanam, directed by Priyadarshan, in which she starred alongside Mohanlal.

Name: Giselli Monteiro
description: Giselli Monteiro is a Brazilian former model and Bollywood actress. She made her film-debut playing Harleen Kaur in the 2009 Bollywood film Love Aaj Kal, directed by Imtiaz Ali.

Name: Gopika
description: Gopika is an Indian film actress, who has predominantly starred in Malayalam films. Starting her career as a model, she ventured into acting with the film Pranayamanithooval. She went on to appear in over 35 films, working in the Tamil, Telugu and Kannada film industries as well.

Name: Gowri Pandit
description: Gowri Pandit is an Indian model and actress. She made her acting debut in the 2005 film Andhrudu. She also appeared in Hero Honda commercial with Barun Sobti.

Name: Gowri Munjal
description: Gowri Munjal is an Indian film actress and model. She has frequently appeared in South Indian films and is probably best known for her performance as Mahalakshmi Somaraju in her debut film Bunny.

Name: Gul Panag
description: Gul Panag is an Indian actress, voice actress, model, and former beauty queen who competed in the Miss Universe pageant. Panag began her career in Bollywood, with the 2003 film Dhoop. Since then, she has worked in films like Jurm and the TV series Kashmeer.

Name: Hansika Motwani
description: Hansika Motwani is an Indian actress who mainly appears in Tamil films. She also appears in Telugu and Hindi films, and has done a number of films in Malayalam and Kannada.

Name: Harini
description: Harini is an Indian film playback singer and classical singer, who sings in Tamil, Hindi, Telugu and Kannada films, working with many leading film composers. She considers legendary singer K. S. Chitra as her inspiration. She is married to another playback singer Tippu.

Name: Haripriya
description: Shruthi Chandrasena, known professionally as Hariprriya, is an Indian film actress and model who chiefly works in Kannada and Telugu films. She has also appeared in several regional films of Tamil, Malayalam, and Tulu cinemas.

Name: Harshika Poonacha
description: Harshika Poonacha is an Indian actress who mainly works in Kannada films and also in Konkani, Kodava, Telugu and Malayalam films. She rose to fame with the 2008 Kannada film PUC.

Name: Hazel Keech
description: Hazel Keech, also known by her married name Gurbasant Kaur, is a British−Mauritian film actress and model who has appeared in Indian television programs and films. She has appeared in Billa and Bodyguard as well as in a Suzuki advertisement. She danced in the Frankfinn Music remix item number, "Kahin Pe Nigahaen".

Name: Heera Rajagopal
description: Heera is a former Indian film actress from 1991 to 1999. She has appeared in several Tamil, Malayalam, Telugu, Kannada and Hindi films.

Name: Helen
description: Helen Anne Richardson Khan, known mononymously as Helen, is an Indian film actress and dancer who is best known for her work in Hindi films. She has received two Filmfare awards and has appeared in over 700 films, and is often cited as one of the most popular nautch dancers of her time.

Name: Hema Malini
description: Hema Malini is an Indian actress, writer, director, producer, dancer and politician. In 1962, she made her acting debut in the Tamil film Ithu Sathiyam. Malini first acted in a main role in Sapno Ka Saudagar, and went on to feature in numerous Bollywood films, primarily as the lead actress.

Name: Honey Rose
description: Honey Rose Varghese is an Indian film actress, who predominantly appears in Malayalam films. She also appeared in a few Tamil, Kannada and Telugu films.

Name: Hrishitaa Bhatt
description: Hrishitaa Bhatt, also spelled as Hrishita Bhat, is an Indian actress and model. She debuted in the film Asoka opposite Shahrukh Khan, but it was Haasil that brought her fame. Bhatt got acclaimed for this role and appeared in films like Ab Tak Chhappan and Jigyaasa, thereafter.

Name: Huma Qureshi
description:
Huma Saleem Qureshi is an Indian film actress and model, who has received three Filmfare Award nominations.
Qureshi obtained a bachelor's degree in History—with honours—from the University of Delhi, while she worked as a theatre actor and model.

Name: Hebah Patel
description: Hebah Patel is an Indian actress and model who works in Kannada, Tamil, and Telugu films.

Name: Ilene Hamann
description: Ilene Hamann is an actress and model from South Africa.

Name: Indrani Haldar
description: Indrani Haldar is an Indian actress who is mostly known for her work in Bengali films. She was conferred with a National Award, three BFJA Awards and two Anandalok Awards.

Name: Iniya
description: Shruti Sawant, better known by her stage name Ineya, is an Indian film actress and model from Trivandrum, Kerala who predominantly appears in Malayalam and Tamil films. She won the Tamil Nadu State Film Award for Best Actress for her role in the Tamil film Vaagai Sooda Vaa.

Name: Isha Chawla
description: Isha Chawla is an Indian film actress, appearing primarily in Telugu films. Chawla made her debut in Tollywood with Prema Kavali opposite debutant Aadi under K. Vijaya Bhaskar's direction.

Name: Isha Sharvani
description: Isha Sharvani is an Indian Contemporary dancer and actress. She is known for her stylistic Indian contemporary and aerial dance performances. She has also starred in Bollywood, Malayalam and Tamil movies.

Name: Isha Koppikar
description: Isha Koppikar is an Indian actress, politician and model who has appeared in Hindi, Tamil, Telugu, Kannada, and Marathi films.

Name: Isha Talwar
description: Isha Talwar is an Indian film actress who predominantly works in Malayalam cinema and Hindi cinema, besides appearing in a few films in Tamil and Telugu cinema. She started out as a model and appeared in various commercials, and later made her film debut with the 2012 Malayalam film Thattathin Marayathu.

Name: Iyshwarya Rajesh
description: Aishwarya Rajesh is an Indian film actress who has appeared in leading roles primarily in Tamil cinema as well as Telugu and Malayalam films with one Hindi film. She started her career as television presenter in a comedy show called Asatha Povathu Yaaru? on Sun TV.

Name: Izabelle Leite
description:
Izabelle Leite is a Brazilian actress and model.
She works predominantly in the Indian film industry.

Name: Ileana D'Cruz
description:
Ileana D'Cruz is an Indian film actress who appears mainly in Telugu and Hindi films, but also in Tamil films.
D'Cruz won the Filmfare Award for Best Female Debut – South for the 2006 Telugu film Devadasu. She established herself in Telugu cinema with films including Pokiri, Jalsa, Kick and Julayi.

Name: Jacqueline Fernandez
description: Jacqueline Fernandez is a Sri Lankan actress, former model, and the winner of the Miss Universe Sri Lanka pageant of 2006 who predominantly works in Bollywood. In 2009, she debuted in Bollywood with the movie Aladin and since then has established a career in the industry.

Name: Jayabharathi
description:
Jayabharathi is an Indian actress who started her career at a young age of 13 in late 1968. She is a two-time winner of the Kerala State Film Award for best actress.
Jayabharathi's first leading role was given by director P. Bhaskaran for his movie Kattukurangu in 1969.

Name: Jayachitra
description: Jayachitra is an actress in South Indian films of the 1970's and 1980's, her work consisting mostly of Tamil and Telugu films.

Name: Jayalalithaa
description: Jayaram Jayalalithaa was an Indian politician and film actress who served six times as the Chief Minister of Tamil Nadu for over fourteen years between 1991 and 2016.

Name: Jaya Bachchan
description: Jaya Bachchan is an Indian film actress and politician. She is currently the Member of Parliament in Rajya Sabha from the Samajwadi Party, notably serving four terms since 2004.

Name: Jaya Prada
description:
Jaya Prada is an Indian film actress and politician.
Jaya Prada is the recipient of three Filmfare Awards South and has starred in many Telugu, Tamil, Hindi, Kannada, Malayalam, Bengali and Marathi films.

Name: Jaya Seal
description:
Jaya Seal is an Indian actress who has acted in several Indian languages. She has appeared in over 15 films.
Seal was born in Guwahati, India. She is a graduate of the National School of Drama. She is acclaimed in Assam for Bihu dance.
Seal has acted in over 15 films and some TV commercials.

Name: Jayasudha
description: Jayasudha Kapoor is an Indian film actress who predominantly appears in Telugu cinema. She was also a former MLA for the Congress in Secunderabad. She has also worked in Tamil, Malayalam, Hindi and Kannada films. She has received seven state Nandi Awards of Andra Pradesh, and seven Filmfare Awards South.

Name: Jayamala
description: Jayamala is an Indian actress and Indian politician. She served as the Minister for Women and Child Development and Empowerment of Differently Abled and Senior Citizens in the Government of Karnataka, by virtue of being a member of the Karnataka Legislative Council.

Name: Jayamalini
description:
Jayamalini is an Indian film actress who is famous for her vamp roles and item numbers.
She acted in more than 500 Tamil, Telugu, Malayalam, Kannada and Hindi movies.

Name: Jennifer Kotwal
description:
Jennifer Kotwal is an Indian actress and model. She was an ace student and completed her studies with a degree in Economics at HR College, Mumbai.
She started her acting career at a very early age of 15 and acted in the lead role in the television teenage drama called Just Mohabbat.

Name: Jennifer Winget
description: Jennifer Winget is an Indian television actress known for her portrayal of Kumud Desai in Saraswatichandra, Maya Mehrotra in Beyhadh and Zoya Siddiqui in Bepannah. In 2019, Winget played Maya Jaisingh in Sony TV's Beyhadh 2.

Name: Jharana Bajracharya
description: Jharna Bajracharya is a Nepalese film actress. She was crowned Miss Nepal in 1997, at the age of sixteen.

Name: Jiya Khan
description:
Jiah Khan was a British-American actress and singer who appeared in the Hindi films. She appeared in three Hindi films from 2007 to 2010 with three of the most successful actors of India cinema.
Born in New York City and raised in London, she was the niece of Pakistani actresses Sangeeta and Kaveeta.

Name: Jugnu Ishiqui
description: Sumann is an Indian actress, model, singer and a dancer.

Name: Juhi Chawla
description: Juhi Chawla Mehta is an Indian actress, model, film producer, and the winner of the 1984 Miss India beauty pageant.

Name: Juhi Babbar
description: Juhi Babbar is an Indian film and television actress. She is also contributing to theatres both as actor and director.

Name: Jyothika
description:
Jyothika Saravanan is an Indian actress who predominantly appears in Tamil films. She also acted in some Telugu, Malayalam, Kannada and Hindi films.
She debuted in Bollywood in the Hindi film Doli Saja Ke Rakhna, directed by Priyadarshan.

Name: Kajal Aggarwal
description:
Kajal Aggarwal is an Indian film actress and model. She has established a career in the Tamil and Telugu film industries and has been nominated for four Filmfare Awards South.
Aggarwal made her acting debut with the 2004 Bollywood film Kyun!

Name: Kajal Kiran
description: Kajal Kiran is a former Indian actress and model, who appeared primarily in Hindi films, as well as acting in Malayalam, Kannada, and Tamil films. Kiran made her debut in 1977, and promptly established herself as a stable actress in Hindi cinema.

Name: Kajjanbai
description: Jahanara Kajjan, also known as Kajjanbai, or "Miss Kajjan", was an Indian singer and actress active during the 1920s and 1930s, often referred to as the "Nightingale of Bengal".

Name: Kajol
description: Kajol, also known by her married name Kajol Devgan, is an Indian film actress, who predominantly works in Hindi cinema. Born into the Mukherjee-Samarth family, she is the daughter of actress Tanuja Samarth and filmmaker Shomu Mukherjee.

Name: Kalki Koechlin
description: Kalki Koechlin is an actress and writer. Although a French citizen, she has lived most of her life in India. Known for her unconventional body of work in the Hindi film industry, she is the recipient of such accolades as a National Film Award, a Filmfare, and two Screen Awards.

Name: Kalpana (Kannada actress)
description: Kalpana, born Sharat Lata, was a Kannada film actress. She was affectionately referred to as Minugu Taare among the film fraternity. She was widely recognised as one of the greatest actresses of Kannada cinema who enjoyed both fan following and critical acclaim.

Name: Kalpana (Malayalam actress)
description:
Kalpana Priyadarshini, better known mononymously as Kalpana, was an Indian film actress who has appeared in South Indian films, predominantly in Malayalam and Tamil films. Kalpana has acted in over 300 films in various South Indian languages.
Kalpana started off her career as a child artist in the late 1970s.

Name: Kalpana Iyer
description: Kalpana Iyer is an Indian actress, singer, and model, who is best known for her works in Hindi cinema throughout the 1980s and 1990s. She appeared in over 100 films, and is accredited for her performances in many item numbers, as well as for her supporting and guest roles in many films.

Name: Kalpana Kartik
description:
Kalpana Kartik is a retired Hindi film actress. She starred in six films in the 1950s. She is the wife of Hindi film actor and film maker Late Dev Anand.
Mona Singha was a beauty queen while studying at St. Bede's College, Shimla.

Name: Kamini Kaushal
description: Kamini Kaushal is a Hindi film and television actress, who is most noted for her roles in films such as Neecha Nagar, which won the 1946 Palme d'Or at Cannes Film Festival and Biraj Bahu, which won her the Filmfare Best Actress Award in 1955.

Name: Kamalinee Mukherjee
description:
Kamalinee Mukherjee is an Indian actress. She has predominantly appeared in Telugu films as well as Malayalam, Tamil, Hindi, Bengali and Kannada language films.
After graduating with a degree in English literature, she completed a workshop on theatre in Mumbai because of her strong background in it.

Name: Kamna Jethmalani
description: Kamna Jethmalani is an Indian film actress. She debuted in 2005 with the Telugu film Premikulu and had her first commercial success with her third feature film Ranam. Subsequently, she played the lead role in a number of Telugu-language films, while also debuting and appearing in Tamil, Malayalam and Kannada films.

Name: Kanaka
description: Kanaka Mahalakshmi, mononymously known as Kanaka, is an Indian film actress active in the Indian film industry during the late 80s to current. She is the daughter of legendary actress Devika and granddaughter of Telugu cinema's first talking film producer Raghupathi Venkaiah Naidu.

Name: Kanakam
description: T. Kanakam was an Indian Telugu drama and film actress and singer between the 1940s and 1960s. She acted in some of the best known and most popular hit films of that period.

Name: Kanchana
description: Puranam Vasundhara devi, known by her stage name Kanchana is a noted Indian actress of the 1960s, 1970s and 1980s. She acted in all four major south Indian languages: Telugu, Tamil, Kannada, and Malayalam, as well as in a few Hindi films.

Name: Kangana Ranaut
description: Kangana Ranaut is an Indian actress and filmmaker who works in Hindi films. The recipient of several awards, including three National Film Awards and four Filmfare Awards, she has featured six times in Forbes India's Celebrity 100 list. In 2020, the Government of India awarded her with the Padma Shri.

Name: Kanika Subramaniam
description: Divya Venkatasubramaniam, better known by her stage name Kaniha or Kanika, is an Indian film actress who predominantly works in Malayalam cinema. Kanika made her debut in the 2002 Tamil film Five Star, she went on to work in other South Indian film industries, including Malayalam, Telugu and Kannada.

Name: Kareena Kapoor
description: Kareena Kapoor Khan is an Indian actress who appears in Hindi films. She is the daughter of actors Randhir Kapoor and Babita, and the younger sister of actress Karisma Kapoor.

Name: Karishma Kapoor
description: Karisma Kapoor is an Indian film actress. One of the most popular Hindi film actresses of the 1990s and early 2000s, she is the recipient of several accolades, including a National Film Award and four Filmfare Awards.

Name: Karishma Tanna
description: Karishma Tanna is an Indian film actress, television actress, model and anchor who predominantly works in Hindi films and shows. She is well known for her roles in Kyunki Saas Bhi Kabhi Bahu Thi, Naagarjuna – Ek Yodha and Qayamat Ki Raat. She was a contestant and first runner-up in the reality show Bigg Boss in 2014.

Name: Karunya Ram
description: Karunya Ram is an Indian film actress who works in Kannada-language cinema. She is know for performing in the 2015 film Vajrakaya.

Name: Karthika Nair
description: Karthika Nair is an Indian film actress in the South Indian film industry. She made her debut in the 2009 Telugu film Josh, opposite Naga Chaitanya. She rose to fame starring in her second and her first successful Tamil film Ko, opposite Jiiva and Piaa Bajpai with ko.

Name: Katrina Kaif
description:
Katrina Kaif is an English actress who works in Hindi films. She has established herself in Bollywood and is one of India's highest-paid actresses.
Born in Hong Kong, Kaif and her family lived in several countries before she moved to London.

Name: Kashmira Shah
description: Kashmira Shah is an Indian actress. Born in Bombay, she is the granddaughter of noted Hindustani classical singer, Anjanibai Lolekar. She has appeared in numerous Hindi and Marathi films. Shah is half Maharashtrian and half Gujarati.

Name: Kausalya
description: Nandini, also known as Kausalya, is an Indian film actress and model, who has starred mainly in Tamil, Malayalam, Telugu and Kannada films. After starting her career as a lead heroine, she has since gone on to portray supporting roles.

Name: Kaviyoor Ponnamma
description: Kaviyoor Ponnamma is an Indian film actress who appears in Malayalam films and television. She began her career performing in theatre dramas before foraying into cinema. She has also acted in TV serials and commercials and has playback singing credits in few films.

Name: Kavya Madhavan
description: Kavya Madhavan is an Indian film actress, who appears predominantly in Malayalam films while having appeared in a few Tamil productions. She made her debut in 1991 as a child artist in Pookkalam Varavayi.

Name: Keerthi Reddy
description: Keerthi Reddy is a former Indian film actress. She has acted in Hindi, Telugu, Tamil and Kannada movies. Her notable work includes Tholi Prema Pyaar Ishq Aur Mohabbat and Arjun.

Name: Keerthi Suresh
description:
Keerthy Suresh is an Indian film actress who appears predominantly in Tamil, Telugu and Malayalam films. She won the National Film Award for Best Actress for portraying actress Savitri in the biopic Mahanati.
Keerthy is the daughter of producer Suresh Kumar and actress Menaka.

Name: Kiara Advani
description: Alia Advani, known professionally as Kiara Advani, is an Indian actress who appears predominantly in Hindi films. After making her film debut with the 2014 poorly received comedy Fugly, Advani had her first commercial success with a brief role in the 2016 sports biopic M.S. Dhoni: The Untold Story.

Name: Kimi Katkar
description: Kimi Katkar is a former actress and model, who worked in Hindi films. She was active throughout the 1980s and the early 1990s, and starred in over 50 films, including Adventures of Tarzan and Hum.

Name: Kimi Verma
description: Kimi Verma, commonly known as Kimi Verma, is an Indian actress and fashion designer.

Name: Kim Sharma
description: Kim Michelle Sharma is an Indian actress and model. She made her acting debut in the Hindi-language film Mohabbatein in 2000.

Name: Kiran Rathod
description: Kiran Rathod is an Indian film actress who has acted in Tamil, Hindi, Malayalam, Telugu and Kannada language films.

Name: Kirron Kher
description: Kirron Anupam Kher is an Indian theatre, film and television actress, singer, entertainment producer, TV talk show host and a member of the Bharatiya Janata Party. In May 2014, she was elected to the Lok Sabha, the lower house of Indian Parliament from Chandigarh.
