Name: Kirat Bhattal
description: Kirat Bhattal, professionally known as Kirat or Keerath, is an Indian film actress. She debuted in modelling roles and then made a breakthrough in the Tamil film industry. She married VJ-actor Gaurav Kapur on 2 November 2014.

Name: Kiran Juneja
description: Kiran Juneja is an Indian actress who works in Hindi cinema.

Name: Kitu Gidwani
description: Kitu Gidwani is an Indian actress and model. She has starred in several movies and serials on Indian television.Her First Superhit Show was Swabhimaan directed by Mahesh Bhatt which aired on Doordarshan from 1995 to 1997. Kitu played the role of Svetlana and became a household name after it.

Name: Koel Mallick
description: Koel Mallick is an Indian film actress who appears in Bengali films. She is the daughter of actor Ranjit Mallick & Deepa Mallick. Her debut film was Nater Guru.

Name: Koel Purie
description: Koel Purie Rinchet is an Indian film actress, producer and TV presenter. She made her debut with Rahul Bose's directorial venture Everybody Says I'm Fine! in 2001 and later featured in Road to Ladakh starring alongside Irrfan Khan. She trained at the Royal Academy of Dramatic Art London.

Name: Koena Mitra
description: Koena Mitra is an Indian actress and model who appears in Bollywood films. She participated on Bigg Boss season 13 as a celebrity contestant.

Name: Komal
description: Komal is an Indian actor in the Kannada film industry, known for comedic roles. He is also a film producer and distributor. Komal made his cinema debut in the year 1992 as a second hero for the movie called Super nan Maga produced by his brother in law N. Srinivas.

Name: Komal Jha
description: Komal Jha is an Indian movie actress and writer. She established a career in Telugu, Kannada, Malayalam and now Hindi film industries and is known for her career transformation from being a civil engineer to an actress, and for her roles in Chinna Cinema.

Name: Konkona Sen Sharma
description: Konkona Sen Sharma is an Indian actress, writer, and director. She has received two National Film Awards and four Filmfare Awards.

Name: K. R. Vijaya
description:
K. R. Vijaya is an Indian actress who has starred Tamil, Malayalam, Telugu, Kannada and Hindi films. She started her career in the 1960s and has acted for more than six decades in South Indian cinema.
K. R.

Name: Krishna Kumari
description:
T. Krishna Kumari was a leading Telugu actress of the 1960s and 1980s. She was the sister of great actress Sowkar Janaki.
Krishna Kumari was a leading actress and a contemporary of Savitri.

Name: Kranti Redkar
description: Kranti Redkar is a Marathi film, television and stage actress.

Name: Kriti Kharbanda
description: Kriti Kharbanda is an Indian film actress and model known for her work in Kannada, Hindi and Telugu language films. She has received accolades including a SIIMA Award and two nominations for the Filmfare Award South.

Name: Kriti Sanon
description: Kriti Sanon is an Indian actress who appears predominantly in Hindi films. She pursued an engineering degree from the Jaypee Institute of Information Technology, after which she briefly worked as a model.

Name: Kushboo
description: Khushbu Sundar is an Indian film actress, producer and television presenter who has acted in more than 200 movies. She is predominantly known for her work in the South Indian film industry. She has received two Tamil Nadu State Film Awards for Best Actress and one Kerala State Film Award – Special Mention.

Name: Kumkum
description: Kumkum, born Zaibunnissa, is an Indian film actress from Hussainabad in Sheikhpura district, Bihar. Her father was Nabab of Hussainabad and belonged to a highly reputed family. She acted in almost 115 films in her career.

Name: Kuljeet Randhawa
description: Kuljeet Randhawa was an Indian model and actress. The former Gladrags model was known for her portrayal of bold and strong women-centric characters. She is best known for her work in TV series C.A.T.S., Special Squad and Kohinoor.

Name: Kulraj Randhawa
description: Kulraj Kaur Randhawa is an Indian actress best known her role as "Kareena" in the popular TV series Kareena Kareena.

Name: Krystle D'Souza
description: Krystle D'Souza is an Indian television actress known for portraying Jeevika Vadhera in Ek Hazaaron Mein Meri Behna Hai. Then she played Sakshi in Ek Nayi Pehchaan. In 2016, she portrayed Raina in Zee TV's Brahmarakshas.

Name: Kainaat Arora

Name: Namitha Pramod
description: Namitha Pramod is an Indian film actress, who appears predominantly in Malayalam films alongside a few Tamil and Telugu films. She made her acting debut in the Malayalam film Traffic.

Name: Nanda
description: Nanda Karnataki known mononymously as Nanda, was an Indian film actress who appeared in Hindi and Marathi films.

Name: Nandana Sen
description: Nandana Sen, is an Indian actress, screenwriter, children's author and child-rights activist. Her first film role in Bollywood was Sanjay Leela Bhansali's Black, starring Rani Mukherjee and Amitabh Bachchan, in which she played the role of Rani's 17-year-old younger sister.

Name: Nandita Chandra
description: Neetu Chandra is an Indian actress, producer and theatre artist. She is also an established classical dancer and an active sportsperson, involved in the promotion of basketball in the country through her close association with the NBA and Taekwondo, being a fourth Dan black-belt.

Name: Nandita Swetha
description: Nandita Swetha is an Indian film actress, who predominantly appears in Tamil & Telugu films. Swetha began her acting career in a Kannada film, Nanda Loves Nanditha. Later she made her acting debut in Tamil Language with the 2012 comedy film Attakathi.

Name: Nandita Das
description: Nandita Das is an Indian actor and director. She has acted in over 40 feature films in ten different languages. Das won accolades for numerous performances, including in Fire, Earth, Bawandar, Kannathil Muthamittal, Azhagi, Kamli, and Before The Rains.

Name: Nargis
description: Nargis Dutt, also known by her stage name Nargis, was an Indian film actress, who starred in classic films of Bollywood.

Name: Nargis Fakhri
description: Nargis Fakhri is an American film actress and model, who mainly appears in Hindi and English-language films. Her first role in film came with the 2011 romantic drama Rockstar, for which she was nominated for Filmfare Award for Best Female Debut.

Name: Anita Hassanandani Reddy
description: Anita Hassanandani is an Indian actress who has acted in multilingual films and serials. She is best known for portraying Shagun Arora in Star Plus's Yeh Hai Mohabbatein and a female shape-shifting serpent named Vishakha Khanna in Colors TV's Naagin.

Name: Nathalia Kaur
description: Nathalia Kaur is a Brazilian model and actress who works in India.

Name: Nauheed Cyrusi
description: Nauheed Cyrusi is an Indian actress, model, and VJ.

Name: Nausheen Sardar Ali
description:
Nausheen Ali Sardar is an Indian television actress and model. She has appeared in many television shows and bollywood movies. Nausheen is still remember for her debut show Kkusum
Sardar also appeared in television reality shows and music albums. She is one among Indian actress who featured in Pakistani movies.

Name: Navaneet Kaur
description: Navaneet Kaur is an Indian film actress who mainly acts in Telugu films. She is elected as Member of Parliament from Amravati, Maharashtra in 2019 Loksabha election as independent candidate.

Name: Navya Nair
description: Dhanya Veena Raju Nair, better known by her stage name Navya Nair, is an Indian film actress who has starred in Malayalam, Tamil, and Kannada films. She is a recipient of 2 Kerala State Film Award for Best Actress, one Filmfare Award for Best Actress - Malayalam and the Kalaimamani award.

Name: Nayanthara
description:
Nayanthara
is an Indian actress who predominantly appears and works in Tamil and Telugu cinema.
She made her acting debut in the 2003 Malayalam film Manassinakkare with Jayaram. She made her debut in Tamil cinema with Ayya and Telugu with Lakshmi. Both were successful.

Name: Nazriya Nazim
description:
Nazriya Nazim is an Indian film actress and producer from Trivandrum, Kerala, who predominantly works in Malayalam Cinema along with a few Tamil films.
She started her career as an anchor on Malayalam television channel Asianet before pursuing a career as an actress.

Name: Neelam
description: Neelam Kothari Soni is an Indian jewellery designer and former actress. She made her acting debut with Jawaani opposite debutant Karan Shah. She then starred opposite Govinda in Love 86, Sindoor, Khudgarz, Hatya, Farz Ki Jung, Taaqatwar and Do Qaidi.

Name: Neelima Azeem
description: Neelima Azeem is an Indian actress and the mother of actors Shahid Kapoor and Ishaan Khatter.

Name: Neena Gupta
description: Neena Gupta is an Indian actress and television director. Known for her work in both art-house and commercial films, she won the National Film Award for Best Supporting Actress for playing a young widow in Woh Chokri.

Name: Neena Kulkarni
description: Neena Kulkarni is an Indian actress. She began her acting career in the 1970s on the Marathi professional stage and Hindi experimental stage, along with fashion shows and modelling simultaneously. She met Pt Satyadev Dubey, her first guru, and went on to be a part of several Hindi productions under his direction.

Name: Neha Bamb
description: Neha Bamb is an Indian actress. She is known for playing the role of Mahi in Maayka and Kaisa Ye Pyar Hai as Kripa.

Name: Neha Dhupia
description: Neha Dhupia is an Indian actress who worked in Hindi, Punjabi, Telugu and Malayalam films. Now she is one of the judges in MTV Roadies. She has won the 2002 Femina Miss India pageant.

Name: Neha Khan
description: Neha Khan is an Indian model and actress who works in Marathi, Malayalam and Bollywood films.

Name: Neha Oberoi
description: Neha Oberoi is an Indian actress who has acted in Tollywood and Bollywood films.

Name: Neha Sharma
description:
Neha Sharma is an Indian actress and model. A native of Bihar, Sharma attended the Mount Carmel School in Bhagalpur and pursued a course in fashion design from the National Institute of Fashion Technology in New Delhi.
Sharma's first role was in the Telugu film Chirutha, released on September 28, 2007.

Name: Neeru Bajwa
description: Neeru Bajwa is a Canadian-born Indian actress, director and producer associated with Punjabi cinema. She started her career in 1998 with Dev Anand's Bollywood film Main Solah Baras Ki and then moved on to working in Indian soap operas and Punjabi films.

Name: Neethu
description: Neethu, also known as Neethu Shetty, is an Indian film actress who predominantly appears in Kannada-language films and a few Tulu and Malayalam films. She won acclaim and praise for movies like Joke Falls, Beru, Photographer -, Koti Chennaya, Gaalipata-, Krishna Nee Late Aagi Baaro and many others.

Name: Neetu Chandra
description: Neetu Chandra is an Indian actress, producer and theatre artist. She is also an established classical dancer and an active sportsperson, involved in the promotion of basketball in the country through her close association with the NBA and Taekwondo, being a fourth Dan black-belt.

Name: Neetu Singh
description: Neetu Kapoor is an Indian film actress who appears in Hindi films. She started acting at the age of 13 under the name Baby Sonia, and made her acting debut in 1966 with the film Suraj.

Name: Nethra Raghuraman
description: Nethra Raghuraman is an Indian actress and model. She has been selected as Look of the Year contest winner for Femina magazine in 1997. She also won the Best female newcomer title at Star Screen Awards in 2000. Her most notable films include Thakshak by Govind Nihalani and Bhopal Express, a David Lynch presentation.

Name: Nicolette Bird
description: Nicolette Bird is an Indian actress and model who has had roles in the Bollywood films Rock On!!, released in 2008, and Striker, released in early 2010. As a model, she has appeared in television commercials and magazine advertisements in India.

Name: Nidhhi Agerwal
description: Nidhhi Agerwal is an Indian model, dancer and actress who appears in Bollywood and Telugu films. In 2017, she made her acting debut in the film Munna Michael. She was Yamaha Fascino Miss Diva 2014 finalist.

Name: Nidhi Subbaiah
description: Nidhi Subbaiah is an Indian film actress and model, who has appeared in various television advertisements and films, she rose to fame by acting in few successful Kannada movies such as Pancharangi and Krishnan Marriage Story.

Name: Niharika Singh
description: Niharika Singh is an Indian film actress and a former Miss India. She won the title of Femina Miss India Earth in 2005 and made her acting debut with the film Miss Lovely, which competed in Un Certain Regard at the 2012 Cannes Film Festival.

Name: Nikesha Patel
description: Nikesha Patel is a British-born-Indian film actress. She was part of several BBC TV shows, before moving to India and entering the film industry. She debuted in the 2010 Telugu film Puli and later went on to work in more than 30 films in Telugu, Kannada, Tamil and Malayalam cinema as a lead.

Name: Niki Aneja
description: Niki Walia is an Indian television and film actress.

Name: Nikita Anand
description: Nikita Anand is an Indian model, actress, television presenter and former beauty queen who was crowned Miss India Universe 2003. She represented India at Miss Universe 2003 where she was unplaced, ending India's eleven-year streak of consecutive placements in Miss Universe, from 1992 through 2002.

Name: Nikita Thukral
description: Nikita Thukral is an Indian film actress and model, who has acted in Kannada, Telugu, Malayalam and Tamil cinemas.

Name: Nikki Galrani
description:
Nikki Galrani is an Indian film actress, model and fashion designer who works predominantly in Tamil and Malayalam films. Her first major commercial successful films are in Malayalam language 1983
, Vellimoonga and in the Tamil language horror film Darling in 2015.

Name: Meera Chopra
description: Meera "Nila" Chopra, is an Indian actress and model who appears in Tamil, Telugu and Hindi films.

Name: Nimisha Sajayan
description: Nimisha Sajayan is an Indian actress in the Malayalam film industry. She won the Kerala State Film Award for Best Actress in 2018 for her roles in the films Oru Kuprasidha Payyan and Chola. Nimisha made her acting debut with the film Thondimuthalum Driksakshiyum directed by Dileesh Pothan.

Name: Nimmi
description: Nawab Banoo, better known by her stage name Nimmi, was an Indian screen actress who achieved stardom in the 1950s and early 1960s in Hindi films. She gained popularity by playing spirited village belle characters, but has appeared in diverse genres such as fantasy and social films.

Name: Nirupa Roy
description: Nirupa Roy was an Indian actress who had appeared in Hindi films. Noted for her portrayals of tragedy and sorrow, Roy was idolized for her acting ability, and was often called the "Queen of Misery" in Hindi film circles. Roy was active from 1946 to 1999, and was best known renowned for playing motherly roles.

Name: Nirmalamma
description: Nirmalamma was an actress in the Telugu film industry of India. She has acted in more than 800 films. She was well known for her grandmother roles in several films.

Name: Nirosha
description: Nirosha Ramki is an Indian film and television actress. She is known for her works predominantly in Tamil, Telugu, Malayalam and Kannada films. After her debut in the blockbuster Tamil film Agni Natchathiram, Nirosha went on to appear in many successful and critically acclaimed films.

Name: Nisha Agarwal
description: Nisha Aggarwal is an Indian film actress who appears in Telugu, Tamil and Malayalam films. She is the younger sister of South Indian actress Kajal Aggarwal.

Name: Nisha Kothari
description: Priyanka Kothari, often credited as Nisha Kothari or Amoha, is an actress and model. She has appeared in Bollywood, Telugu, Tamil and Kannada films. She has frequently appeared in Ram Gopal Varma films.

Name: Nithya Das
description: Nithya Das is an Indian film actress best known for her Malayalam films. She was active in the industry during the early-2000s.

Name: Nithya Menen
description: Nithya Menen is an Indian film actress and playback singer who appears in Malayalam, Tamil, Kannada, Telugu and Hindi films where she has established herself as a leading actress. She is recipient of three Filmfare Awards for the Telugu films Gunde Jaari Gallanthayyinde, Malli Malli Idi Rani Roju and Mersal in Tamil.

Name: Nivedita Jain
description: Nivedita Jain was a beauty contestant and an actress who appeared in Kannada films. She was crowned Miss Bangalore in 1994. She made her debut as actress in the 1996 released film, Shivaranjini.

Name: Nivedita Joshi Saraf
description: Nivedita Saraf is an Indian actress who worked in Marathi and Hindi film industry of the late 1980s and early 1990s. She is married to Marathi and Hindi films actor Ashok Saraf. Since July 2019, she is playing a lead role in the Marathi-language serial Aagabai Sasubai on Zee Marathi.

Name: Noor Jehan
description:
Noor Jehan, also spelled Noorjehan,
, also known by her honorific title Malika-e-Tarannum, the queen of melody, was a Pakistani playback singer and actress who worked first in British India and then in Pakistan. Her career spanned more than six decades.

Name: Nora Fatehi
description: Nora Fatehi is a Canadian dancer, model, actress and singer who has mainly appeared in Hindi films. She has also starred in Malayalam and Telugu films.

Name: Nutan
description: Nutan Samarth, better known as Nutan, was an Indian film actress. In a career spanning nearly four decades, she appeared in more than 70 Hindi films, many in starring roles.

Name: Nimrat Kaur
description: Nimrat Kaur is an Indian actress. She began her career as a print model and went on to act in theater. After brief appearances in a few films, Kaur starred in Anurag Kashyap's production Peddlers, which was screened at the 2012 Cannes Film Festival.

Name: Nyla Usha
description: Nyla Usha Gopakumar is an Indian film actress, television host, and radio jockey from Trivandrum, Kerala. After working for nearly a decade as an RJ at Hit 96.7 in Dubai, she made her acting debut in 2013 with Kunjananthante Kada.

Name: Oviya Helen
description: Helen Nelson, better known professionally by her stage name Oviya, is an Indian model and film actress who has worked predominantly in the Tamil and Malayalam film industries.

Name: Padmapriya
description: Padmapriya Janakiraman, better known mononymously as Padmapriya, is an Indian film actress and model. She is a trained bharatanatyam dancer, Padmapriya made her acting debut in the Telugu language film Seenu Vasanthi Lakshmi in 2003, following which she appeared in a number of Malayalam and Tamil language films.

Name: Padma Khanna
description: Padma Khanna is an Indian actress, dancer and director. She appeared mainly in Hindi and Bhojpuri films in the 1970s and 1980s. She is most remembered for her role in the film Saudagar with Amitabh Bachchan and also as Queen Kaikeyi in Ramanand Sagar's epic series Ramayan.

Name: Padma Kumta
description: Padma Kumta or Padma Kumata was an Indian film actress in the Kannada film industry. Some of the notable films of Padma Kumta as an actress include Chomana Dudi, Bayalu Daari, Phalitamsha, Avasthe and Arivu. She died of cardiac arrest.

Name: Padma Lakshmi
description:
Padma Parvati Lakshmi Vaidynathan, known professionally as Padma Lakshmi, is an American author, actress, model, and television host. She is the host of the US cooking competition program Top Chef.
She has hosted the show continuously since season 2, with season 17 being the latest.

Name: Padmini Kolhapure
description: Padmini Kolhapure is an Indian actress and singer, who works primarily in Hindi films. She began acting in 1972 at the age of 7, and her early works included Zindagi and Dream Girl. She then made her official film debut with the film Satyam Shivam Sundaram, starring as Young Roopa.

Name: Padmini
description: Padmini was an Indian Actress and trained Bharathanatyam dancer, who acted in over 250 Indian films. She acted in Tamil, Hindi, Malayalam Telugu and Russian language films. She was a popular actress of her time. Padmini, with her elder sister Lalitha and her younger sister Ragini, were called the "Travancore sisters".

Name: Pallavi Joshi
description: Pallavi Joshi is an Indian film and television actress. She is a recipient of Special Jury Award at the National Film Awards.

Name: Pallavi Kulkarni
description: Pallavi Kulkarni is an Indian television actress.

Name: Pallavi Subhash
description: Pallavi Subhash Shirke is an Indian film and television actress. A Maharashtrian model turned actress, she has started her career with Marathi plays, films and TV shows, then appeared in Hindi TV shows.

Name: Pallavi Sharda
description: Pallavi Sharda is an Australian-Indian film actress. She has worked in Hindi films like My Name Is Khan, Dus Tola, Besharam, Hawaizaada and Begum Jaan.

Name: Panchi Bora
description: Panchi Bora is an Indian television actress and model from Assam. She plays lead roles in the series Kayamath and Kitni Mast Hai Zindagi, before working in the Telugu film industry.

Name: Pandari Bai
description: Pandari Bai was a prominent actress of South Indian languages films, mostly in Kannada language during the 1950s, 1960s and 1970s. She is considered Kannada cinema's first successful heroine. She has acted as both heroine and mother to stalwarts such as Rajkumar, MGR and Sivaji Ganesan.

Name: Pakhi Tyrewala
description: Paakhi A Tyrewala is the stage name of Punarnava Mehta an Indian writer-cum-director, who debuted in mainstream Bollywood in 2002 with the film Yeh Kya Ho Raha Hai?, in which she is credited with real name Punarnava Mehta.

Name: Paoli Dam
description: Paoli Dam is an Indian actress who started her career with the Bengali television serial Jibon Niye Khela. She then worked in Bengali television serials such as Tithir Atithi and Sonar Harin; the former ran for six years on ETV Bangla.

Name: Parineeti Chopra
description: Parineeti Chopra is an Indian actress and singer who appears in Hindi films. Chopra is a recipient of several accolades, including a Filmfare and National Film Award.

Name: Parminder Nagra
description: Parminder Kaur Nagra is an English film and television actress. She is known for playing Jess Bhamra in the film Bend It Like Beckham, and as Dr. Neela Rasgotra in the NBC medical drama series ER from 2003 to 2009.

Name: Parul Chauhan
description: Parul Chauhan Thakkar is an Indian television actress popular for her portrayal as Ragini Sharma in Sapna Babul Ka...Bidaai and Swarna Chopra in Yeh Rishta Kya Kehlata Hai. Before venturing into acting, she did modelling. In 2009, she participated as a contestant in the reality series Jhalak Dikhhla Jaa 3.

Name: Parul Gulati
description:
Parul Gulati is an Indian actress who has appeared in several Punjabi films. She is a trained actor who has studied at Royal Academy of Dramatic Art, London.
In Gulati appeared in the TV series P.O.W.- Bandi Yuddh Ke, and Haq Se Web Series - An adaptation of Little Women, Gulati plays "Jo March".

Name: Parul Yadav
description: Parul Yadav is an Indian film actress and producer, who has appeared in South Indian films, primarily in Kannada along with a few Malayalam and Tamil films. She made her acting debut with Tamil film Dreams, starring Dhanush and Diya.

Name: Parvathy Jayaram
description:
Ashwathy Kurup, better known by her stage name Parvathy, is an Indian film actress and classical dancer, who appeared in Malayalam films.
Parvathy was a popular actress in Malayalam cinema during the late-1980s and early-1990s. Her first film was directed by Lenin Rajendran, but was shelved and never released.

Name: Parvathy Nair
description: Parvati Nair is an Indian model and actress who works in the South Indian film industry. Born into a Malayali family in Abu Dhabi, she trained as a software professional while pursuing a career in modelling, before becoming an actress.

Name: Parvathy Omanakuttan
description: Parvathy Omanakuttan is an Indian actress, model and beauty pageant titleholder who was crowned Miss India 2008 and later became first runner-up at Miss World 2008. She was also awarded the titles of Miss World Asia & Oceania at the Miss World 2008 competition.

Name: Parvati Melton
description: Parvathi Melton is an American actress and former model of partial Indian descent. She mainly works in the Telugu film industry. She appeared in several Telugu and Malayalam movies. She acted with Raja in the film Vennela, which turned out to be a success. She acted in the super hit Malayalam film Hallo with Mohanlal.

Name: Parvati Menon
description: Parvathy Thiruvothu is an Indian film actress who appears predominantly in Malayalam films in addition to a few Tamil, Kannada films and a Hindi film. Hailing from Kozhikode, Kerala, she made her debut in the 2006 Malayalam film Out of Syllabus.

Name: Parveen Babi
description: Parveen Babi was an Indian film actress, model, and an interior designer. She is most remembered for her appearances in several commercially-successful films, and playing mostly bold roles throughout the 1970s and early 1980s.

Name: Patience Cooper
description: Patience Cooper was an India born Pakistani film actress. An Anglo-Indian from Calcutta, Cooper had a successful career in both silent and sound films. She was one of the early superstars of Bollywood.

Name: Patralekha
description: Patralekha Mishra Paul is an Indian film actress. Her father, a chartered accountant, wanted her to follow in his footsteps, but she was interested in acting. She made her debut with director Hansal Mehta's Hindi film CityLights, alongside Rajkummar Rao.

Name: Payal Rohatgi
description: Payal Rohatgi is an Indian actress and reality TV performer who appears in Bollywood films. She was a contestant in the reality show Bigg Boss in 2008. She has made controversial remarks on social media on multiple occasions.

Name: Payel Sarkar
description:
Payel Sarkar
is an Indian actress who has appeared in Bengali films and Hindi television.

Name: Payal Ghosh
description: Payal Ghosh is an Indian celebrity actress who has recently made her debut into Bollywood.

Name: Perizaad Zorabian
description: Perizaad Zorabian is an Indian actress. Her film debut was with Nagesh Kukunoor's Bollywood Calling and she gained international recognition for her role as Jenny in Subhash Ghai's Joggers' Park.

Name: Pia Bajpai
description: Pia Bajpiee is an Indian film actress and model, who appears in Tamil, Telugu, Malayalam, Hindi and English. She is best known for her performances as Roshini in Venkat Prabhu's comedy Goa and Saro in K. V. Anand's political thriller Ko Leadrole. Before acting in films, she had been a model in commercials.

Name: Pooja Batra
description: Pooja Batra is an Indian actress and model. She was crowned Femina Miss India International in 1993.

Name: Pooja Bedi
description: Pooja Bedi is a former Bollywood actress, television talk show host and newspaper columnist. She is the daughter of actor Kabir Bedi and the late Protima Bedi. Pooja participated in the popular reality show, Bigg Boss in 2011.

Name: Pooja Bhatt
description:
Pooja Bhatt is an Indian film director, actress, voice over artist, model and film maker. The recipient of several accolades, including two National Film Awards.
Born into the Bhatt family, she is the daughter of Indian filmmaker, Mahesh Bhatt.

Name: Pooja Gandhi
description: Pooja Gandhi is an Indian actress and producer, who mainly works in Kannada language films and also appears in Tamil, Malayalam, Bengali and Hindi.

Name: Pooja Hegde
description: Pooja Hegde is an Indian model and film actress who appears mainly in Telugu and Hindi films. A former beauty pageant contestant, she was crowned as the second runner-up at the Miss Universe India 2010 competition, before going on to make her acting debut in Mysskin's Tamil superhero film Mugamoodi.

Name: Pooja Kanwal
description:
Pooja Kanwal is an Indian actress. She appeared in Palampur Express where she portrayed the lead role of Pawni.
She is a daughter of Anita Kanwal.
On 6 November 2009 she married a Bandra-based jeweler, Avinash Mehtani.

Name: Pooja Lokesh
description: Pavitra Lokesh is an Indian film and television actress. She appears primarily in Kannada and Telugu films playing supporting roles. The daughter of stage and film actor Mysore Lokesh, she made her film debut at 16 and has since appeared in over 150 Kannada films.

Name: Pooja Umashankar
description: Pooja Gauthami Umashankar, mononymously known as Pooja, is an Indian-Sri Lankan film actress, who has appeared in Tamil films as well as Sinhalese, Malayalam and amateur films.

Name: Poonam Bajwa
description: Poonam Bajwa is an Indian film actress and model who appears in Malayalam, Telugu, Tamil and Kannada films. She made her acting debut in 2005 with the Telugu film Modati Cinema, after that she was featured in more Telugu film, such as Boss. Her debut Tamil movie was Seval.

Name: Poonam Jhawer
description: Poonam Jhawer is an Indian model, Bollywood film maker, singer and actress.

Name: Poonam Dhillon
description: Poonam Dhillon is an Indian Hindi-language film, theatre and TV actress and politician. A former Femina Miss India. She is best known for her 1979 film Noorie and for her six films with Rajesh Khanna; Red Rose, Dard, Nishaan, Zamana, Awam and Jai Shiv Shankar.

Name: Poonam Kaur
description: Poonam Kaur is an Indian actress and model from Hyderabad, who appears in Telugu, Tamil, and Malayalam films.

Name: Poonam Pandey
description: Poonam Pandey is an Indian film actress known for her works in Bollywood and Telugu cinema. She began her career as a model. She became one of the top nine contestants of the Gladrags Manhunt and Megamodel Contest and appeared on the cover page of the fashion magazine.

Name: Prayaga Martin
description:
Prayaga Rose Martin
is an Indian film actress from Kerala, who predominantly works in Malayalam cinema. She debuted as a child actor in Sagar Alias Jacky Reloaded in 2009. She rose to prominence after the Tamil film Pisaasu, which garnered her recognition.

Name: Prachi Desai
description: Prachi Desai is an Indian film actress and former television actress. She started her television career as lead protagonist in the successful TV drama Kasamh Se on Zee TV. She made her Bollywood debut in the 2008 film Rock On!!.

Name: Pratibha Sinha
description: Pratibha Sinha is a former Indian actress working in Bollywood movies and the daughter of Mala Sinha, a former Bollywood actress herself and Mala Sinha was one of the highest paid and most popular actress back in late 50s 60s and 70s.

Name: Pranitha Subhash
description: Pranitha Subhash is an Indian film actress and model who predominantly appears in Kannada, Telugu and Tamil films. She was raised in Bangalore and pursued a career in modelling before plunging into films.

Name: Preetha Vijayakumar
description: Preetha Hari is an Indian film actress in the Tamil, Malayalam and Telugu film industries. Her parents are noted actors Vijayakumar and Manjula. She is married to Tamil film director Hari.

Name: Preeti Jhangiani
description: Preeti Jhangiani is an Indian model and actress. She is known for her work in Mohabbatein.

Name: Preity Zinta
description: Preity G Zinta is an Indian film actress and entrepreneur. After graduating with degrees in English honours and criminal psychology, Zinta made her acting debut in Dil Se.. in 1998, followed by a role in Soldier in the same year.

Name: Prema
description: Prema is an Indian film actress. She has worked as a lead actress in numerous Kannada films besides Telugu, Tamil and Malayalam films. She has appeared in many commercially successful and critically acclaimed feature films.

Name: Prema Narayan
description: Prema Narayan is a Model and Bollywood actress-dancer. She has acted in Hindi and Bengali cinema. She was the Femina Miss India World 1971. and represented India at Miss World 1971.

Name: Priti Sapru
description: Priti Sapru, is an actress of Punjabi cinema. She featured in a number of films including Nimmo, Yaari Jat Di and Qurbani Jatt Di among others, with actors Veerendra, Gurdas Maan and Raj Babbar.

Name: Priya Anand
description: Priya Anand is an Indian film actress and model who appears in Tamil, Malayalam, Hindi, Telugu and Kannada films. After pursuing higher studies in the US, she began a career in modelling in 2008 before making her acting debut in the Tamil film Vaamanan and then her Telugu debut in Leader a year later.

Name: Priya Bapat
description: Priya Bapat is an Indian actress who works in Hindi and Marathi films. She is best known for her roles in the movies Kaksparsh and Aamhi Doghi, for which she won the Best Actress award at the Screen ...

Name: Priya Gill
description: Priya Gill is an Indian actress. She appeared mainly in Hindi films, along with a film each in Punjabi, Malayalam, Tamil, Bhojpuri and two movies in Telugu. She was second runner-up in Miss India 1995.

Name: Priya Lal
description: Priyanka Lalaji better known as Priyaa Lal; is a British Indian actress. Her first appearance was in the Malayalam film Janakan in 2010, directed by N. R. Sanjeev with Mohanlal and Suresh Gopi. She played the lead character Seetha /Anu, as Gopi's and Kaveri's daughter in the movie.

Name: Priya Raman
description: Priya Raman is a Malayalam actress and film producer. She has appeared in Malayalam, Tamil, Telugu and Kannada cinema and in television serials of both languages. Her first film was the Rajnikanth-produced film Valli, in 1993. Her second film. Arthana, directed by I. V.

Name: Priya Rajvansh
description: Priya Rajvansh, born Vera Sunder Singh, was an Indian film actress, who is known for her performance in Hindi films like Heer Raanjha and Hanste Zakhm, amongst a handful of films she did during her career.

Name: Priya Wal
description: Priya Wal is an Indian television actress, known for her roles in television series such as Remix, Kahaani Ghar Ghar Kii, and Pyaar Kii Ye Ek Kahaani.

Name: Priyamani
description: Priya Vasudev Mani Iyer, professionally credited as Priyamani, is an Indian film actress and former model, who works in Telugu, Kannada, Tamil, Malayalam and Hindi-language films. She is the recipient of a National Film Award for Best Actress and three Filmfare Awards in different-language films.

Name: Priyanka Bassi
description: Priyanka Bassi is an Indian television actress popularly known for her famous act as Cadet Naina Singh Ahluwalia in the popular soap Left Right Left. She is originally from Delhi and has also attended Barry John's Theatre Group.

Name: Priyanka Chopra
description: Priyanka Chopra Jonas is an Indian actress, singer, film producer, and the winner of the Miss World 2000 pageant. One of India's highest-paid and most popular celebrities, Chopra has received numerous awards, including a National Film Award and five Filmfare Awards.

Name: Priyanka Nair

description: Surbhi Jyoti is an Indian television actress known for her portrayal of Zoya in Qubool Hai and Bela in Naagin 3.

Name: Supriya Devi
description: Supriya Devi was an Indian actress who is known for her work in Bengali cinema for more than 50 years. She is best known for her portrayal of Neeta in Ritwik Ghatak's Bengali film Megha Dhaka Tara. She was conferred the Filmfare Award and the BFJA Award twice.

Name: Supriya Karnik
description: Supriya Karnik is an Indian television actress and character artist in Bollywood, known for her negative roles. She is highly popular for portraying comic roles in super-hit movies Mujhse Shaadi Karogi and Welcome.

Name: Supriya Pathak
description: Supriya Pathak Kapur is an Indian actress of film, television and stage. She is mostly popular for playing the role of Hansa Parekh in the Khichdi franchise, and for her vitriolic avatar of "Dhankor Baa" in Sanjay Leela Bhansali's Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram-Leela.

Name: Supriya Pilgaonkar
description: Supriya Pilgaonkar, often known by her screen name Supriya, is a Hindi/Marathi actress. She is married to Hindi/Marathi actor Sachin Pilgaonkar.

Name: Suraiya
description:
Suraiya Jamal Sheikh, popularly known by the mononym Suraiya, was a popular Indian Hindi/Hindustani film actress and playback singer in Bollywood. She was active from 1936 to 1963.
In a career spanning from 1936 to 1963, Suraiya acted in 67 films and sang 338 songs.

Name: Surveen Chawla
description: Surveen Chawla is an Indian film actress and dancer. She started her career with television soap operas in the earlier days and ended up in appearing in the films. She is known for her roles in movies and serials like Hate Story 2, Ugly, Parched and 24 etc. along with many others films.

Name: Suryakantham
description: Suryakantham was an Indian actress in Tollywood. She was regarded as one of the finest actors of Indian Cinema and was popular for playing the role of a cruel mother-in-law in most of her movies.

Name: Sushma Reddy
description: Sushama Reddy is an Indian model, VJ, actress and producer.

Name: Sushmita Sen
description: Sushmita Sen is an Indian film actress and model who was crowned Femina Miss India in 1994 and Miss Universe 1994 contest at the age of 18. Sen is the first Indian woman to win the competition and has primarily worked in Hindi films.

Name: Sumalatha
description: Sumalatha is an Indian film actress, politician who is the current Member of Parliament in the Lok Sabha from Mandya, Karnataka. She has acted in more than 220 films in Telugu, Malayalam, Kannada, Tamil and Hindi.

Name: Swati Reddy
description: Swathi Reddy is an Indian film actress and television presenter who predominantly works in Telugu Cinema along with Tamil and Malayalam films. Her nickname Colors Swathi comes from her stint in the Telugu television show Colours, which was telecast on Maa TV.

Name: Swapna
description: Swapna Barman is an Indian heptathlete. She won the gold medal at 2018 Asian Games and was placed first in the Heptathlon at the 2017 Asian Athletics Championships. In August 2019, she was honoured with the Arjun Award.

Name: Swaroop Sampat
description: Swaroop Sampat is an Indian actress who has acted in several Hindi language films such as Naram Garam and Nakhuda and is known for her performance in television serials like Yeh Jo Hai Zindagi. She won the Miss India contest in 1979 and represented India at Miss Universe 1979.

Name: Swastika Mukherjee
description:
Swastika Mukherjee is an Indian actress and the daughter of Late Santu Mukhopadhyay.
Mukherjee made her screen debut with Devdasi, a Bengali TV series. She made her big screen debut with Hemanter Pakhi. Her first leading role came with Mastan. She made her Bollywood debut with Mumbai Cutting.

Name: Sandhya
description: Revathy, known by her stage name "Kadhal" Sandhya, is an Indian film actress who acts primarily in Tamil, Malayalam, Telugu and Kannada films. She made her debut as an actress in the 2004 Tamil film Kaadhal, her performance in which earned her a Filmfare Award and Special Jury Award by Government of Tamil Nadu.

Name: Tabu
description: Tabassum Fatima Hashmi, known by the mononym Tabu, is an Indian film actress primarily working in Hindi films, in addition to Telugu, Tamil, Malayalam, English, Bengali and Marathi films.

Name: Tanaaz Irani
description: Tanaaz Irani is an Indian actress. She has acted in Bollywood films and Hindi television serials. She has also been credited as Tanaaz Lal, her maiden name, and Tanaaz Currim. She participated in Bigg Boss 3 in 2009.

Name: Tanisha
description: Tanisha Mukerji is an Indian film actress known for her works in Indian movies, Bollywood and Telugu and Tamil films. Part of the Mukherjee-Samarth family, she is the daughter of filmmaker Shomu Mukherjee and actress Tanuja Samarth and the younger sister of Bollywood actress Kajol.

Name: Tanushree Dutta
description: Tanushree Dutta is an Indian model and actress who primarily appears in Bollywood movies. Dutta was the recipient of the Femina Miss India Universe title in 2004 at age 20. During the same year at the Miss Universe beauty pageant, she was among the top ten finalists.

Name: Tanuja
description: Tanuja Samarth, popularly known as Tanuja, is an Indian film actress, who predominantly works in the Hindi film industry.

Name: Tanu Roy
description: Tanu Roy is an Indian film actress and model. A Bengali by birth, she has predominantly appeared in Telugu films apart from some Tamil, Malayalam, Bengali and Kannada films. She is mostly known for her item numbers in films like Mass and Hero. She is known for her role in the Malayalam movie Ee Adutha Kalathu.

Name: Tanvi Azmi
description: Tanvi Azmi is an Indian film and television actress.

Name: Tamannaah Bhatia
description: Tamanna Bhatia, known professionally as Tamannaah, is an Indian actress who predominantly appears in Tamil and Telugu films. She has also appeared in several Hindi films. In addition to acting, she also participates in stage shows and is a prominent celebrity endorser for brands and products.

Name: Tapsee Pannu
description: Taapsee Pannu is an Indian actress who works primarily in Telugu, Tamil and Hindi films. Pannu made her acting debut with the 2010 Telugu film Jhummandi Naadam and then starred in the 2011 films Aadukalam, Vastadu Naa Raju and Mr. Perfect.

Name: Tara
description: Tara Sutaria is an Indian actress. She started her television career as a child artist in 2010 with Disney India's Big Bada Boom and went on to star in the channel's sitcoms The Suite Life of Karan & Kabir and Oye Jassie.

Name: Tara Anuradha
description: Anuradha, known by her stage name Tara, is an Indian actress and politician. As an actress, she is known for her work in Kannada cinema. She joined the Bharatiya Janata Party in 2009 and is currently a nominated member of the Karnataka Legislative Council.

Name: Tara Deshpande
description: Tara Deshpande is an Indian actress, writer, former model and MTV VJ. Tara hosted a show called Kab Kyon Kahaan on Zee TV, along with Parth and then with Vinay Jain in the early 1990s. She appeared in several acclaimed films such as Sudhir Mishra's Is Raat Ki Subah Nahin and Kaizad Gustad's Bombay Boys.

Name: Tara D'Souza
description: Tara Concepta D'Souza, commonly known as Tara D'Souza, is an Indian film actress and model, known for her work in the films Mujhse Fraaandship Karoge and Mere Brother Ki Dulhan.

Name: Tara Sharma
description: Tara Sharma is a British-Indian actress, entrepreneur, creator, and producer.

Name: Taruni Sachdev
description: Taruni Sachdev was an Indian model and child actress, best known for her work in television advertisements and films. She made appearances in Rasna advertisements and the Bollywood film Paa, playing Amitabh Bachchan's classmate.

Name: Tejaswi Madivada
description: Tejaswi Madivada is an Indian film actress and model, who works predominantly in the Telugu film industry. A dance tutor turned actress, she made her acting debut in 2013 with Seethamma Vaakitlo Sirimalle Chettu and became noted after starring in Ice Cream.

Name: Tena Desae
description: Tina Desai is an Indian actress and model. She debuted with the 2011 thriller Yeh Faasley, and went on to star in the action comedy Sahi Dhandhe Galat Bande, before making her foreign debut in 2012 in the comedy-drama The Best Exotic Marigold Hotel. She is also known for her main role in the Netflix series Sense8.

Name: Tia Bajpai
description: Tia Bajpai is an Indian singer, television and film actress. She made her film debut in 2011 with Vikram Bhatt's film Haunted - 3D, and appeared in 1920: Evil Returns and Baankey Ki Crazy Baraat. She also participated in Sa Re Ga Ma Pa Challenge 2005.

Name: Tina Munim
description: Tina Anil Ambani is a former Bollywood actress and chairperson of the Mumbai-based Kokilaben Dhirubhai Ambani Hospital, Harmony for Silvers Foundation and Harmony Art Foundation.

Name: Tina Dutta
description: Tina Datta, also spelled Tinaa Dattaa, is an Indian film and television actress. She played the lead role of Ichcha Veer Singh Bundela in Uttaran and participated in the reality show Fear Factor: Khatron Ke Khiladi 7. She has also played the role of Dhamini in Karmaphal Daata Shani.

Name: Tisca Chopra
description: Tisca Chopra is an Indian actress, author and film producer. She has acted in over 45 feature films in different languages with many eminent directors like Aamir Khan, Prakash Jha, Madhur Bhandarkar, Abhinay Deo, Nagesh Kukunoor and Anup Singh.

Name: Trisha Krishnan
description: Trisha Krishnan, known mononymously as Trisha, is an Indian film actress and model, who primarily works in Tamil and Telugu language films. She was noticed after winning several beauty pageants like the Miss Madras contest, which marked her entry into filmdom.

Name: Tulip Joshi
description: Tulip Joshi is an Indian actress who has appeared in Hindi, Kannada, Malayalam and Telugu films.

Name: Tun Tun
description: Tun Tun was the screen name of Indian playback singer and actress-comedian, Uma Devi Khatri, who was called "Hindi cinema's first-ever comedienne".

Name: Twinkle Khanna
description:
Twinkle Khanna is a well-known author, newspaper columnist, interior designer, film producer and a former film actress.
In 2015, she released her first non-fiction book, "MrsFunnybones" which was declared a bestseller, making Khanna India’s highest-selling woman writer that year.

Name: Udhayathara
description: Udhayathara is an Indian film actress, who predominantly acts in Tamil and Malayalam cinema but also appears in Kannada and Telugu films.

Name: Udaya Chandrika
description: Udaya Chandrika, better known by her screen name Radha, is an Indian film actress known mostly for her work in Tamil and Telugu films. She has also acted in few Malayalam, Kannada and Hindi. She was one of the top south Indian heroine for a decade from 1981 to 1991. Her elder sister Ambika, was also an actress.

Name: Udita Goswami
description: Udita Goswami is an Indian actress who works in Hindi cinema.

Name: Ujjwala Raut
description: Ujjwala Raut is an Indian supermodel. She is the most successful overseas supermodel from india.She was one of five daughters and was born in Mumbai.

Name: Uma
description: Uma is an Indian film actress who appeared in regional Indian language films.

Name: Uma Padmanabhan
description: Uma Padmanabhan is a Tamil film and television actress.

Name: Umashree
description: Umashree is an Indian actress and politician. She is known for her portrayal of film roles spoken in the Kannada language, particularly comic roles. She received National Film Award for Best Actress for her role as Gulabi in the 2008 Kannada movie Gulabi Talkies.

Name: Usha Chavan
description: Usha Chavan is an Indian actress working mainly in Marathi movies. She has also had roles in Telugu movies such as Durdabitta, and in the Hindi film Shirdi Ke Sai Baba. She has done many films with actor Dada Kondke and the duo was well liked n appreciated by the audience

Name: Urmila Matondkar
description: Urmila Matondkar, is an Indian actress. Known for her work in Hindi films, in addition to Telugu, Tamil, Malayalam and Marathi cinema, she has received numerous accolades, including the Filmfare Award and the Nandi Award.

Name: Urmila Kanitkar
description: Urmilla Kanetkar Kothare is an Indian film actress in Marathi cinema, and television. She is known for her roles in the Marathi films Duniyadari, Shubha Mangal Saavadhan, Ti Saddhya Kay Karte and Hindi TV serials Maayka and Mera Sasural and the Marathi serials Asambhav, Uun Paus and Goshta Eka Lagnachi.

Name: Urvashi
description:
Urvashi Rautela is an Indian film actress and model who appears in Bollywood films. Rautela was crowned
Miss Diva - 2015 and represented India at the Miss Universe 2015 pageant.
She made her Bollywood debut with Singh Saab the Great and appeared in films like Sanam Re, Great Grand Masti, Hate Story 4 and Pagalpanti

Name: Urvashi Dholakia
description: Urvashi Dholakia is an Indian television actress best known for portraying Komolika Majumdar in Kasautii Zindagii Kay and Queen Iravati in Chandrakanta, winning Bigg Boss 6 and participating in Nach Baliye 9.

Name: Urvashi Sharma
description: Urvashi Sharma is an Indian Bollywood actress and model, born in Delhi.

Name: Usha Kiran
description: Usha Kiran was an Indian film actress. In a career spanning over four decades, she acted in over 50 Hindi and Marathi films, notably Daag, Patita, Baadbaan, Chupke Chupke, Mili and Bawarchi. She was also the Sheriff of Mumbai during 1996 and 1997.

Name: Usha Nadkarni
description: Usha Nadkarni is an Indian television and Bollywood, Marathi actress who is best known for her role of Savita Deshmukh in the popular show Pavitra Rishta, for which she was nominated in Zee Rishtey Awards as "Best Evil Mother-In-Law". She is a contestant on the Marathi version of Bigg Boss in 2018.

Name: Ulka Gupta
description: Ulka Gupta is an Indian film and television actress. She is popularly known as Manu as she played the role of Manu in the Zee TV soap Jhansi Ki Rani until leap and later Ulka made a re-entry to the same show as Kaali. Her debut film is a Tollywood movie, Andhra Pori, in which she plays the lead character, Prashanti.

Name: Upasna Singh
description: Upasana Singh is an Indian actress and stand-up comedian. Singh is known for her role as a deaf-mute in the 1997 film Judaai. She played the character of "Bua" in the TV show Comedy Nights with Kapil and Tarawanti in the mad comedy show Nadaniyaan on BIG Magic.

Name: Urvashi Rautela
description:
Urvashi Rautela is an Indian film actress and model who appears in Bollywood films. Rautela was crowned
Miss Diva - 2015 and represented India at the Miss Universe 2015 pageant.
She made her Bollywood debut with Singh Saab the Great and appeared in films like Sanam Re, Great Grand Masti, Hate Story 4 and Pagalpanti

Name: Vaani Kapoor
description: Vaani Kapoor is an Indian actress known for her work in Bollywood films produced by Yash Raj Films. She made her film debut in the 2013 romantic comedy Shuddh Desi Romance, a critical and commercial success, which earned her Filmfare Award for Best Female Debut.

Name: Vanitha Vijayakumar
description: Vanitha Vijayakumar is an Indian film actress, who has appeared in Tamil, Malayalam, and Telugu language films.

Name: Vadivukkarasi
description: Vadivukkarasi is an Indian film and Tamil television actress. She made her acting debut in the Tamil film Sigappu Rojakkal and has acted in more than 350 films and 10 television serials in Tamil, Telugu, Kannada and Malayalam. Film director A. P. Nagarajan is her maternal uncle.

Name: Vaishali Desai
description: Vaishali Desai is an Indian model and actress. She won the Indian title of Miss International. She debuted in the film Kal Kissne Dekha.

Name: Vaishali Kasaravalli
description: Vaishali Kasaravalli was a noted Kannada actress, television serial director and costume designer.

Name: Vandana Gupte
description: Vandana Gupte is a Marathi stage actress who has also performed television and film roles.

Name: Vanishree
description: Vanisri, is an Indian film actress known for her works predominately in Telugu, Tamil, Kannada and Hindi films. In a film career spanning 40 years, she has received three Filmfare Awards South, including the Nandi Awards and the Tamil Nadu State Film Award.

Name: Vanisri
description: Vanisri, is an Indian film actress known for her works predominately in Telugu, Tamil, Kannada and Hindi films. In a film career spanning 40 years, she has received three Filmfare Awards South, including the Nandi Awards and the Tamil Nadu State Film Award.

Name: Vani Viswanath
description: Vani Viswanath is an Indian film actress. She joined in Telugu Desam Party in Andhra Pradesh. In 2000, Vani won the Kerala State Film Award for Second Best Actress for her performance in Susanna, directed by T. V. Chandran. She was termed as Mollywood's "Action Queen".

Name: Vaishnavi Mahant
description: Vaishnavi Mahant is an Indian film and TV actress who is best known for playing Geeta Vishwas in Mukesh Khanna's television series Shaktimaan, telecasted on Doordarshan. She has acted in various Bollywood films such as Bambai Ka Babu, opposite Saif Ali Khan, Ladlaa and Barsaat Ki Raat.

Name: Vrushika Mehta
description: Vrushika Mehta is an Indian actress and professional dancer known for playing Sharon Rai Prakash in Channel V's Dil Dosti Dance and Puchki/Devika Ghosh in Zee TV's Yeh Teri Galiyan.

Name: Varalaxmi Sarathkumar
description: Varalaxmi Sarathkumar is an Indian who has appeared in Tamil, Malayalam and Kannada films. She made her debut with the Tamil film Podaa Podi, portraying a London-based dancer.

Name: Varsha Bollamma
description: Varsha Bollamma is an Indian actress in Tamil, Malayalam, and Telugu films. She made her acting debut in the Tamil film Sathuran. Her works include Yaanum Theeyavan, Kalyanam, and Seemathurai.

Name: Varsha Usgaonkar
description: Varsha Usgaonkar is an Indian film actress from Goa, who has worked in various Bollywood and Marathi movies as the leading lady. During the 1990s, she was the most popular actress in Marathi cinema.

Name: Vasundhara Das
description: Vasundhara Das is an Indian singer, actress, composer, entrepreneur, speaker, songwriter and environmental activist. Vasundhara's films include Hey Ram, Monsoon Wedding, Citizen, Ravana Prabhu, Lankesh Patrike and several others. Vasundhara has worked with composers such as A. R.

Name: Veda Sastry
description: Archana Shastry is an Indian film actress, working in Telugu cinema, Tamil cinema and Kannada cinema. She was one of the contestants in the first season of Bigg Boss - Telugu, hosted by N. T. Rama Rao Jr.. Shastry is a trained classical dancer in Kuchipudi dance form and performs in India, USA, UK and Malayasia.

Name: Veena Malik
description: Zahida Malik, better known as Veena Malik, is a Pakistani actress, TV host, reality television personality and model who has appeared in Pakistani and Bollywood films. Veena made her film debut in 2000 with Sajjad Gul's Tere Pyar Mein.

Name: Veena (actress)
description: Veena, also known as Veena Kumari, real name Tajour Sultana, was an Indian actress.

Name: Vidhubala
description:
Vidhubala is a former Malayalam film actress who started her career in the mid-1970s and retired when she was at the peak of her career.
Currently Vidhubala hosts a well accepted family reality show Kadhayallithu Jeevitham in Amrita TV.

Name: Vidya Balan
description: Vidya Balan is an Indian actress. Known for pioneering a change in the portrayal of women in Hindi cinema with her roles in female-led films, she is the recipient of several awards, including a National Film Award and six Filmfare Awards. She was awarded the Padma Shri by the Government of India in 2014.

Name: Vithika Sheru
description: Jeedigunta Vithika, also known as Vithika Sheru, is an Indian actress, who has acted in Telugu, Tamil and Kannada. She was one of the participants in the Bigg Boss Telugu 3 show.

Name: Vidya Malvade
description: Vidya Malvade is an Indian actress.

Name: Vidya Sinha
description: Vidya Sinha was an Indian film actress who has acted in Hindi films, most known for Rajnigandha, Chhoti Si Baat and Pati Patni Aur Woh. She started her career as a model and won the Miss Bombay title. Her first movie was Raja Kaka opposite Kiran Kumar.

Name: Vishakha Singh
description:
Vishakha Singh is an Indian film actress, producer and entrepreneur.
She has appeared in many South Indian language films, before starring in Bollywood projects with director Ashutosh Gowariker's 2010 period piece Khelein Hum Jee Jaan Sey, alongside Abhishek Bachchan and Deepika Padukone.

Name: Vijeta Pandit
description: Vijayta Pandit is an Indian film actress and playback singer, most famous for her first film Love Story.

Name: Vijayalakshmi
description: Vijayalakshmi is an Indian film actress who has predominantly appeared in Tamil language films. As the daughter of film director Agathiyan, Vijayalakshmi made her acting debut as a timid girl in Venkat ...

Name: Vijayashanti
description: Vijayashanti Satti is an Indian film actress, producer and a politician. In a film career spanning 30 years, she has acted in over 180 feature films in a variety of roles in various Indian languages including Telugu, Tamil, Malayalam, Kannada and Hindi.

Name: Vimala Raman
description: Vimala Raman is an Australian actress and model who has worked in all South Indian film industries, and predominantly appears in Telugu and Malayalam films. Born in Australia, she is a Kannadiga from Bangalore and made her debut in 2005 with the Tamil film Poi.

Name: Vinaya Prasad
description: Vinaya Prasad, born as Vinaya Bhat, is a popular film and television actress in South India who has primarily featured in Kannada and Malayalam films and TV series besides acting in Tamil and Telugu language films. She has won the State Best Actress Award for her performances in Aathanka and Bannada Hejje.

Name: Vyjayantimala
description: Vyjayanthimala is an Indian film actress, Bharathanatyam dancer, Carnatic singer, dance choreographer and parliamentarian. She was the highest paid actress of her time.

Name: Waheeda Rehman
description: Waheeda Rehman is an Indian actress and dancer who has appeared in mainly Hindi films, as well as Telugu, Tamil, Bengali and Malayalam films. She is noted for her contributions to different genres of films and different roles from the 1950s, 1960s, and early 1970s.

Name: Yagna Shetty
description: Yagna Shetty is an Indian actress known for her work in Kannada cinema. She made her debut in the 2007 film Ondu Preethiya Kathe, following which she appeared in Eddelu Manjunatha, a performance that won her a Filmfare Special Award.

Name: Yami Gautam
description: Yami Gautam is an Indian actress who predominantly appears in Hindi films. Gautam came to prominence after starring in a series of Fair & Lovely commercials. She later starred in television shows such as Chand Ke Paar Chalo and Yeh Pyar Na Hoga Kam. Following this, she appeared in several South Indian films.

Name: Yogeeta Bali
description: Yogeeta Bali Chakraborty is a former Indian Hindi film actress. She was active in the late 1960s and through the 1970s.

Name: Yana Gupta
description: Yana Gupta is a Czech model, actress and wife of Ing. Petr Brhel, author who worked in Mumbai.

Name: Yukta Mookhey
description: Yukta Mookhey is an Indian actress, model and beauty pageant titleholder. She represented India at Miss World 1999 and eventually won the contest, becoming the fourth Indian woman to win Miss World. She has worked in few Hindi films, and is involved in various social movements as a civic activist.

Name: Yuvika Chaudhary
description: Yuvika Chaudhary is an Indian actress who has appeared in Bollywood films such as Om Shanti Om, Summer 2007 and Toh Baat Pakki. In 2009, she also acted in a Kannada movie, Maleyali Jotheyali, in a lead role opposite Ganesh. In 2015, she was a contestant in Colors TV's reality show Bigg Boss 9.

Name: Zaira Wasim
description: Zaira Wasim is a former Indian actress who worked in Hindi films. The recipient of numerous accolades, including a Filmfare Award and a National Film Award, Wasim was honoured with the National Child Award for Exceptional Achievement by Ram Nath Kovind, the President of India, at a ceremony in New Delhi in 2017.

Name: Zarina Wahab
description:
Zarina Wahab is an Indian actress who predominantly worked in Hindi and Malayalam films. Known for critically acclaimed roles in Chitchor and Gopal Krishna in the 1970s in Bollywood and later in early 1980s with hits like
Madanolsavam, Chamaram, Palangal and Adaminte Makan Abu establishing herself in Malayalam Cinema.

Name: Zarine Khan
description: Zareen Khan, also known as Zarine Khan, is an Indian actress and model who mainly works in the Hindi film industry, though has also appeared in Punjabi films.

Name: Zeenat Aman
description: Zeenat Khan, better known as Zeenat Aman, is an Indian actress and model, who is best known for her work in Bollywood films, and is widely considered to be a highly influential actress in Indian cinema.

Name: Zoya Khan
description: Zoya Khan is an Indian actress, anchor and host. She began her career as an anchor and print model. She has done numerous commercials mostly for the print media and has also walked the ramp. She gained attention in a Delhi beauty pageant, where she won titles of Miss Beautiful Smile & smooth skin.

Name: Zubeida
description: Zubeida Begum Dhanrajgir was an Indian film actress. She acted in the first Indian talkie movie Alam Ara. Her credits include early hits Devdas, and Sagar Movietone's first talkie, Meri Jaan.

Name: Zaheeda
description:
Zaheeda Hussain, commonly known by her mononym Zaheeda, is an Indian film actress, who is best known for appearing in films such as Anokhi Raat, Gambler, and Prem Pujari.
Born in Mumbai, she is daughter of Akhtar Hussain, who was film producer and son of director Jaddanbai.
